WEBVTT

1
00:00:43.293 --> 00:00:46.421
BASED ON A TRUE STORY

2
00:00:53.720 --> 00:00:55.347
Ladies and gentlemen...

3
00:00:55.472 --> 00:00:56.849
WELCOME TO LAS VEGAS

4
00:00:56.974 --> 00:00:59.268
you very sensibly
skip the casinos...

5
00:00:59.393 --> 00:01:00.477
ELECTRONICS FAIR

6
00:01:00.602 --> 00:01:05.482
Where you are always at a disadvantage. and come
to the place where it is always prize.

7
00:01:05.607 --> 00:01:09.820
Technology is the future.
and computer games are at the forefront of it.

8
00:01:11.321 --> 00:01:14.199
So come try out the next world hit.

9
00:01:14.324 --> 00:01:15.743
PLAYER 1

10
00:01:15.868 --> 00:01:19.204
Play Go. the Asian favorite.

11
00:01:19.329 --> 00:01:22.124
Rights available everywhere.
except in Japan.

12
00:01:22.875 --> 00:01:24.126
How do you make it?

13
00:01:24.251 --> 00:01:26.628
Go. Go. Go. Playing pot?
It's like playing chess.

14
00:01:26.753 --> 00:01:28.672
But then much more difficult.

15
00:01:30.007 --> 00:01:34.344
Go didn't run so smoothly.
Even my saleswoman got distracted.

16
00:01:34.469 --> 00:01:38.640
And I know how many excuses
bank managers hear every day.

17
00:01:38.765 --> 00:01:41.685
But this is not an excuse. This is an opportunity.

18
00:01:42.394 --> 00:01:47.107
Indeed. this minor setback
was perhaps our greatest windfall.

19
00:01:48.025 --> 00:01:49.568
Yes.
- Tracy.

20
00:01:49.693 --> 00:01:51.695
Tracy. What are you doing?

21
00:01:51.820 --> 00:01:56.408
I invited her over to see
whether our new game is catching on with the ladies.

22
00:01:58.827 --> 00:02:01.789
Come. Tracy.
I'll pay you to sell my game.

23
00:02:01.914 --> 00:02:04.333
Easy. Henk. This game is cool.

24
00:02:04.458 --> 00:02:06.543
What is it called?
- Tetris.

25
00:02:07.503 --> 00:02:08.723
Tetris.

26
00:02:09.128 --> 00:02:10.089
I don't get it.

27
00:02:10.214 --> 00:02:13.842
A combination of 'tetra'.
Greek for "four

28
00:02:14.593 --> 00:02:18.097
All pieces consist of four cubes.
And "tennis.

29
00:02:18.222 --> 00:02:19.515
Tennis?
- Tennis.

30
00:02:19.640 --> 00:02:22.935
Yes. the Russian inventor
apparently likes tennis.

31
00:02:24.061 --> 00:02:26.480
Here. Henk. Try.

32
00:02:45.791 --> 00:02:49.670
Is this written in Pascal or C?
- That's classified.

33
00:02:49.795 --> 00:02:50.754
What do you think?

34
00:02:50.879 --> 00:02:54.466
It was "the most beautiful thing I had ever seen.
- I've heard that before.

35
00:02:54.591 --> 00:02:58.053
No. This is different from Go.
Not comparable.

36
00:02:58.178 --> 00:03:01.265
I've heard that before. too.
- Okay. fine. But. Eddie...

37
00:03:02.474 --> 00:03:06.395
I played Tetris for five minutes.

38
00:03:08.772 --> 00:03:10.941
I still dream about falling cubes now.

39
00:03:12.568 --> 00:03:17.030
This game is more than addictive.
It stays with you.

40
00:03:17.948 --> 00:03:22.786
This is poetry. Art and mathematics
working together enchantingly. It is...

41
00:03:25.122 --> 00:03:26.415
the perfect game.

42
00:03:27.583 --> 00:03:30.711
Why are you telling me that?

43
00:03:30.836 --> 00:03:32.546
Do you have the rights to this?

44
00:03:32.671 --> 00:03:36.842
Mirrorsoft controls all rights
to all platforms. worldwide.

45
00:03:36.967 --> 00:03:38.719
Is Japan available?

46
00:03:39.803 --> 00:03:45.267
You are now sitting across from the licensee
of Tetris in Japan. for the PC....

47
00:03:46.310 --> 00:03:47.530
game consoles...

48
00:03:48.437 --> 00:03:49.657
and gaming halls.

49
00:03:50.355 --> 00:03:51.575
Are you kidding?

50
00:03:52.524 --> 00:03:56.904
So with the money you owe this bank
owed for your failed game

51
00:03:59.448 --> 00:04:04.870
Did you buy another game?
- Correct. But. Eddie. this is different.

52
00:04:05.621 --> 00:04:07.247
Tetris is already a success.

53
00:04:07.372 --> 00:04:08.999
Where.
- In Russia.

54
00:04:10.250 --> 00:04:14.546
Henk.
there is no game business in Russia.

55
00:04:14.671 --> 00:04:18.591
I know. Let me finish.

56
00:04:20.886 --> 00:04:21.845
PLAYER 2

57
00:04:21.970 --> 00:04:26.308
It all started with a man
named Aleksey Leonidovich Pazhitnov....

58
00:04:26.433 --> 00:04:28.018
four years ago.

59
00:04:30.145 --> 00:04:34.775
By day. he was a programmer
at the Soviet Computer Science Center.

60
00:04:36.527 --> 00:04:40.781
But at night
he programmed games for fun.

61
00:04:51.917 --> 00:04:57.047
His computer. a piece of antique
Soviet junk called an Electronika 60...

62
00:04:57.172 --> 00:04:59.425
Didn't even have a video card.

63
00:04:59.550 --> 00:05:03.178
His falling cubes
still consisted of square brackets.

64
00:05:05.514 --> 00:05:10.060
Together with some colleagues. he made
the game compatible with IBM computers.

65
00:05:11.228 --> 00:05:16.775
So color graphics. 8-bit music
and floppies that people copied for free.

66
00:05:16.900 --> 00:05:17.860
MOSKOU

67
00:05:17.985 --> 00:05:20.404
It went off like wildfire.

68
00:05:22.114 --> 00:05:26.952
But don't forget
that this happened in the Soviet Union.

69
00:05:28.453 --> 00:05:29.830
Nothing just comes out.

70
00:05:30.581 --> 00:05:33.458
Before that. an entrepreneur had to
go there himself.

71
00:05:34.042 --> 00:05:35.262
Who?

72
00:05:35.794 --> 00:05:37.014
You?

73
00:05:37.838 --> 00:05:41.717
Jesus. No. I'm not that tapped out.
It was Robert Stein.

74
00:05:41.842 --> 00:05:43.302
PLAYER 3

75
00:05:46.096 --> 00:05:47.514
Two years ago.

76
00:05:49.641 --> 00:05:51.852
Welcome back to Budapest.

77
00:05:51.977 --> 00:05:57.524
As a self-employed person from London
he searched Eastern Europe for games....

78
00:05:57.649 --> 00:06:00.819
which he could
could resell at a profit.

79
00:06:02.070 --> 00:06:03.697
Know already. Boring.

80
00:06:09.953 --> 00:06:12.581
What is this?
- This one is not ours.

81
00:06:15.542 --> 00:06:18.086
COMPUTER SCIENCE CENTER MOSCOW

82
00:06:22.591 --> 00:06:27.137
Stein. That idiot
keeps wasting our fax paper.

83
00:06:29.181 --> 00:06:30.401
What does it say?

84
00:06:30.933 --> 00:06:33.018
He wants the license for my game.

85
00:06:34.603 --> 00:06:35.823
Can I sell that?

86
00:06:37.773 --> 00:06:40.150
We'll just have to check with ELORG.

87
00:06:41.360 --> 00:06:43.237
Yes. you may. Fax it.

88
00:06:50.077 --> 00:06:51.036
WE AGREE

89
00:06:51.161 --> 00:06:57.459
With the license arranged
he went to London. to Robert Maxwell.

90
00:06:57.584 --> 00:06:58.804
PLAYER 4

91
00:06:59.962 --> 00:07:01.880
One year ago...

92
00:07:03.006 --> 00:07:06.176
Mr. Stein. nice to meet you.
Robert Maxwell.

93
00:07:06.301 --> 00:07:07.678
Pleasant.

94
00:07:07.803 --> 00:07:09.763
The Robert Maxwell?

95
00:07:10.889 --> 00:07:13.684
The stone-faced media mogul?
- The one and only.

96
00:07:13.809 --> 00:07:18.105
Okay. Now that's the type of businessman
we bankers are happy with.

97
00:07:18.230 --> 00:07:20.566
Maxwell repays his debts.

98
00:07:21.984 --> 00:07:23.902
Does he do distribution?

99
00:07:24.027 --> 00:07:25.279
Sort of.

100
00:07:25.404 --> 00:07:26.905
This is my son.

101
00:07:27.030 --> 00:07:28.824
I can imagine myself.

102
00:07:30.158 --> 00:07:31.378
PLAYER 5

103
00:07:32.327 --> 00:07:34.621
Kevin Maxwell. director of Mirrorsoft.

104
00:07:34.746 --> 00:07:36.540
Pleasant. Kevin.

105
00:07:36.665 --> 00:07:38.876
Just say "Mr. Maxwell." sir.

106
00:07:41.962 --> 00:07:45.716
Anyway. gentlemen:
in my opinion. we have something to celebrate.

107
00:07:46.425 --> 00:07:47.645
Kevin.

108
00:07:48.427 --> 00:07:51.763
The first computer game
to come through the Iron Curtain.

109
00:07:52.639 --> 00:07:55.851
My old crony Mikhail Gorbachev
must be proud.

110
00:07:56.810 --> 00:07:59.438
We start with licenses
for computer games...

111
00:07:59.563 --> 00:08:04.735
And then video games. arcade games.
board games. the whole lot.

112
00:08:12.075 --> 00:08:13.035
Continue.

113
00:08:13.160 --> 00:08:16.955
Nice. Because you'll never believe
where I was yesterday.

114
00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:19.666
GISTERED

115
00:08:29.343 --> 00:08:32.136
Day. Henk Rogers. Bullet-Proof Software.

116
00:08:32.261 --> 00:08:35.765
I have an appointment
with your director. Hiroshi Yamauchi.

117
00:08:35.890 --> 00:08:37.110
Rogers?

118
00:08:38.519 --> 00:08:43.023
You are not in it.
- Oh. okay. I understand.

119
00:08:43.690 --> 00:08:44.910
Thank you.

120
00:08:46.985 --> 00:08:49.321
May I use your toilet before I go?

121
00:08:49.446 --> 00:08:50.739
On the left?
- Yes.

122
00:08:50.864 --> 00:08:52.366
Okay. thank you.

123
00:09:09.049 --> 00:09:13.220
Hi. I have an appointment with Mr. Yamauchi.
- Mr. Rogers. you can't be here.

124
00:09:13.345 --> 00:09:14.763
Mr. Yamauchi is not here.

125
00:09:14.888 --> 00:09:17.683
I saw him this morning
And his car is outside.

126
00:09:20.394 --> 00:09:24.648
Who is this?
- Day. Henk Rogers. Bullet-Proof Software.

127
00:09:39.830 --> 00:09:41.999
Not bad.
- Really?

128
00:09:45.794 --> 00:09:48.422
We buy it for 500.000.

129
00:09:52.217 --> 00:09:54.094
Five hundred grand?

130
00:09:54.219 --> 00:09:56.847
Henk. I'll buy you a drink.

131
00:09:57.973 --> 00:09:59.391
I declined.

132
00:10:01.393 --> 00:10:02.644
You have what?

133
00:10:03.645 --> 00:10:07.482
Are you out of your mind?
- I have bigger ambitions. Eddie.

134
00:10:08.567 --> 00:10:10.068
That's why I'm here.

135
00:10:12.821 --> 00:10:15.699
I'll bring it out
and pay all the start-up costs.

136
00:10:18.410 --> 00:10:21.955
We do something like that ourselves.
We don't use outside partners.

137
00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:25.334
You don't do that often. that's right.

138
00:10:26.793 --> 00:10:28.504
But you make exceptions.

139
00:10:30.339 --> 00:10:35.719
Because you also know that partners help
to achieve great things.

140
00:10:37.804 --> 00:10:39.890
That's why Mario has Luigi.

141
00:10:43.560 --> 00:10:45.312
That's why Zelda has Link.

142
00:10:50.734 --> 00:10:55.113
That's why Mike Tyson...
the one guy he hits in Punch-Out...

143
00:11:06.375 --> 00:11:09.128
We want 200.000 cassettes.

144
00:11:09.253 --> 00:11:11.713
Do you want two million dollars?
- Well no.

145
00:11:13.340 --> 00:11:14.675
I was already startled.

146
00:11:14.800 --> 00:11:17.052
I need three million.

147
00:11:18.762 --> 00:11:21.139
Is that the joke? You want money from me?

148
00:11:22.432 --> 00:11:24.059
How do you come up with three million?

149
00:11:24.184 --> 00:11:27.396
I need two million
for Nintendo cassettes...

150
00:11:27.521 --> 00:11:28.647
GAME COMPUTER

151
00:11:28.772 --> 00:11:32.985
And one million for arcade cabinets.
I have the rights for that too. don't I?

152
00:11:33.110 --> 00:11:34.069
CUT IN

153
00:11:34.194 --> 00:11:38.574
Video arcades work with cash.
That's fast. That's fine for us.

154
00:11:41.285 --> 00:11:43.829
This is the opportunity of a lifetime. Eddie.

155
00:11:45.163 --> 00:11:47.082
Nintendo let me publish it.

156
00:11:47.958 --> 00:11:50.961
Nintendo. This is a gold mine.

157
00:11:54.715 --> 00:11:56.884
Are you really that convinced?
- Yes. Of course.

158
00:11:57.009 --> 00:11:58.761
Then I'll raise your interest rate.
- Fine.

159
00:11:58.886 --> 00:12:00.846
And I want your house as collateral.
- Fine.

160
00:12:00.971 --> 00:12:02.848
Miss one payment and 'tis ours.

161
00:12:03.682 --> 00:12:04.902
Fine.

162
00:12:06.310 --> 00:12:08.854
Don't you want to discuss that with your wife?

163
00:12:10.647 --> 00:12:14.109
Akemi is the chief financial officer
of our company.

164
00:12:15.152 --> 00:12:16.486
She stands behind it.

165
00:12:17.279 --> 00:12:20.949
TOKIO

166
00:12:21.074 --> 00:12:22.451
MORTGAGE AGREEMENT

167
00:12:22.576 --> 00:12:24.369
This is not what you promised.

168
00:12:24.494 --> 00:12:28.290
True. But you know
how little imagination bankers have.

169
00:12:30.042 --> 00:12:34.254
Pioneers must bet everything.
- Not literally.

170
00:12:35.881 --> 00:12:37.101
Listen.

171
00:12:42.471 --> 00:12:47.351
Has it ever been this quiet before
in our apartment?

172
00:12:55.776 --> 00:12:56.996
Maya?

173
00:12:58.946 --> 00:13:00.280
What do you think?

174
00:13:01.031 --> 00:13:03.534
It's great. can we keep it?

175
00:13:05.786 --> 00:13:08.705
This is going to work. I promise.

176
00:13:11.333 --> 00:13:13.252
Can you deliver on that promise?

177
00:13:14.670 --> 00:13:18.465
If we do this. we are the boss.

178
00:13:19.258 --> 00:13:20.478
So. yes...

179
00:13:22.719 --> 00:13:24.221
I can.

180
00:13:35.107 --> 00:13:36.327
Yoshi.

181
00:13:38.902 --> 00:13:40.122
Itsuko.

182
00:13:42.114 --> 00:13:43.334
People.

183
00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:49.872
As of now. we are a big failure.

184
00:13:55.544 --> 00:13:58.922
As of now. we are a major publisher.

185
00:14:06.013 --> 00:14:07.556
MOSKOU

186
00:14:12.394 --> 00:14:13.812
From bottom to top.

187
00:14:14.229 --> 00:14:19.776
Watch your feet. and then move up.
- Playing tennis in the winter. Impressive.

188
00:14:23.322 --> 00:14:27.075
Valentin Trifonov.
Central Committee. Communist Party.

189
00:14:30.370 --> 00:14:34.750
I wanted to meet the man
who almost destroyed the Soviet Union.

190
00:14:36.710 --> 00:14:37.930
Excuse me?

191
00:14:38.086 --> 00:14:39.380
Your game.

192
00:14:39.505 --> 00:14:42.758
Officials throughout the Soviet Union
played it for hours.

193
00:14:43.467 --> 00:14:45.344
They were no longer doing any work.

194
00:14:45.802 --> 00:14:49.848
We had to write a program
that keeps it off our computers.

195
00:14:53.268 --> 00:14:56.522
I hear that a Westerner
you pay for the license.

196
00:14:57.189 --> 00:14:59.983
Are you already making a profit?

197
00:15:03.195 --> 00:15:08.367
It would be strange if such a popular game
does not make a profit abroad.

198
00:15:10.994 --> 00:15:12.412
Then there is trouble.

199
00:15:14.831 --> 00:15:17.668
Dad. can we continue?
- Hold on.

200
00:15:20.170 --> 00:15:22.965
I'm sorry for the interruption.

201
00:15:23.090 --> 00:15:25.968
Congratulations again.
You have earned it.

202
00:15:40.858 --> 00:15:43.569
Bullet-Proof. with Henk.
- Mr. Rogers?

203
00:15:43.694 --> 00:15:46.113
Kevin Maxwell. director of Mirrorsoft.

204
00:15:46.989 --> 00:15:49.324
Oh. hi. Kevin.

205
00:15:50.951 --> 00:15:53.620
Make that "Mr. Maxwell." sir.

206
00:15:53.745 --> 00:15:59.043
You bought the PC. game console and arcade
rights for Tetris purchased in Japan?

207
00:15:59.168 --> 00:16:00.169
That's right.

208
00:16:00.294 --> 00:16:03.255
We have given Sega
the arcade rights in Japan.

209
00:16:04.381 --> 00:16:05.340
What. When.

210
00:16:05.465 --> 00:16:08.093
I got a deal with your guy in Vegas.

211
00:16:08.218 --> 00:16:10.387
I am not concerned with the details.

212
00:16:10.512 --> 00:16:12.973
I paid.
We signed a contract.

213
00:16:13.098 --> 00:16:16.101
No. no. You have signed.
I haven't yet.

214
00:16:16.810 --> 00:16:18.896
That's why I'm calling.
- This is bullshit. Kevin.

215
00:16:19.021 --> 00:16:22.274
No. "Mr. Maxwell.
- This is bullshit. Mr. Maxwell.

216
00:16:22.399 --> 00:16:23.984
This is how I go bankrupt.

217
00:16:24.109 --> 00:16:26.445
Do you still want those PC and gaming computer privileges?

218
00:16:28.071 --> 00:16:29.291
Yes.

219
00:16:30.365 --> 00:16:31.585
I thought so. too.

220
00:16:38.957 --> 00:16:40.584
We lost the arcade rights.

221
00:16:45.297 --> 00:16:48.467
Hiro-san.
Just stop with that arcade prototype.

222
00:16:48.800 --> 00:16:54.139
Don't worry. all of you.
We still have the gaming rights.

223
00:16:54.640 --> 00:16:59.436
Henk has an appointment with Nintendo.
It will be fine. Okay.

224
00:17:04.983 --> 00:17:06.777
Congratulations.

225
00:17:06.902 --> 00:17:11.114
I wanted to give you your own copy
of Tetris before they sold out.

226
00:17:13.700 --> 00:17:14.920
Thank you.

227
00:17:15.577 --> 00:17:19.164
Do you know.
that everything goes well in Super Mario...

228
00:17:20.123 --> 00:17:23.752
and then all of a sudden
a plant that spits fire at you?

229
00:17:25.838 --> 00:17:32.302
The problem is: Kevin Maxwell
spat fire at us.

230
00:17:34.179 --> 00:17:38.725
I don't have arcade rights. I need a
mushroom to stay alive.

231
00:17:43.689 --> 00:17:47.484
May I please have an advance
on my Nintendo fee?

232
00:17:54.283 --> 00:17:57.745
Mr. Yamauchi would like to introduce you
to his colleagues in Seattle.

233
00:17:57.870 --> 00:17:59.872
We may be able to help you.

234
00:18:01.039 --> 00:18:02.791
Pros.

235
00:18:06.753 --> 00:18:08.797
TOKIO

236
00:18:21.602 --> 00:18:22.895
Okay. guys.

237
00:18:23.020 --> 00:18:29.610
Why don't we go clean up our room
before mom comes home? Yeah.

238
00:18:29.735 --> 00:18:32.071
Next month is my school concert.

239
00:18:32.196 --> 00:18:35.449
I only now know what song I'm singing
And I need to practice.

240
00:18:36.116 --> 00:18:39.244
But I need help.
- Sorry. honey.

241
00:18:39.745 --> 00:18:42.372
Dad needs to prepare
for his business trip.

242
00:18:42.873 --> 00:18:46.543
But I'm looking forward
to your performance. okay?

243
00:18:47.711 --> 00:18:50.589
I have to pack. Come. children. clean up.

244
00:19:05.312 --> 00:19:06.532
The Sanctuary.

245
00:19:10.901 --> 00:19:13.529
Day. Henk Rogers. Bullet-Proof Software.

246
00:19:13.654 --> 00:19:16.657
I'm honored to be here.
- Bye. Henk.

247
00:19:16.782 --> 00:19:18.951
Minoru Arakawa.
director. Nintendo of America.

248
00:19:19.076 --> 00:19:21.370
I know.
- Henk Rogers. Shit.

249
00:19:21.495 --> 00:19:24.790
Welcome. Howard Lincoln.
vice president. legal counsel.

250
00:19:24.915 --> 00:19:28.252
Your cowboy reputation precedes you.

251
00:19:28.377 --> 00:19:30.462
Here. Just sign this.

252
00:19:31.129 --> 00:19:33.382
A confidentiality agreement? Why?

253
00:19:33.507 --> 00:19:37.136
Because only ten people on earth
have seen what you are about to see

254
00:19:37.261 --> 00:19:40.305
and to be honest:
we don't trust you.

255
00:19:55.445 --> 00:19:56.655
8-bit graphics?

256
00:19:56.780 --> 00:20:01.702
Yes. and a brand new Sharp
LR35902 processor of 4.19 megahertz...

257
00:20:01.827 --> 00:20:03.871
with eight KB of internal RAM.

258
00:20:05.664 --> 00:20:06.884
Impressive.

259
00:20:08.709 --> 00:20:09.668
No color screen?

260
00:20:09.793 --> 00:20:12.671
Then he needs eight batteries
and it becomes too expensive.

261
00:20:13.255 --> 00:20:17.634
This provides 30 hours of play time.
for only $89.

262
00:20:20.137 --> 00:20:21.357
What is it called?

263
00:20:23.348 --> 00:20:24.850
It's called a Game Boy.

264
00:20:27.311 --> 00:20:28.770
Try it out.

265
00:20:51.293 --> 00:20:52.503
It comes out in June.

266
00:20:52.628 --> 00:20:55.506
And we want publishers like you to
arrange new games.

267
00:20:55.631 --> 00:20:59.468
So Mario is included?
- Yes. Our best series.

268
00:21:01.720 --> 00:21:03.889
This is programmed in C. right?

269
00:21:05.015 --> 00:21:09.645
How many pixels?
- 160 by 144. How so?

270
00:21:24.243 --> 00:21:27.204
It's not perfect. but this is the idea.

271
00:21:37.548 --> 00:21:41.176
If you want to sell hundreds of thousands of
Game Boys want to sell to children...

272
00:21:42.553 --> 00:21:44.054
Then deliver Mario with it.

273
00:21:44.805 --> 00:21:50.269
But if you want to sell millions of
Game Boys want to sell to anyone...

274
00:21:50.394 --> 00:21:52.604
young and old. all over the world....

275
00:21:54.398 --> 00:21:56.066
Then deliver Tetris with it.

276
00:22:02.531 --> 00:22:03.751
Are you arranging the rights?

277
00:22:12.082 --> 00:22:13.302
LONDON

278
00:22:19.590 --> 00:22:23.719
Hi. I'm Henk Rogers.
I want to speak to Kevin Maxwell.

279
00:22:23.844 --> 00:22:27.431
Do you have an appointment?
- No. It's a surprise.

280
00:22:27.556 --> 00:22:30.851
I am doing my best.
- Don't tell nonsense. You are not doing your best.

281
00:22:30.976 --> 00:22:36.023
No. on a scale of one to "your best
you do even less than zero. Not a damn thing.

282
00:22:36.607 --> 00:22:40.360
The Russians are not stupid.
They know that Tetris sells well.

283
00:22:40.485 --> 00:22:43.530
But they don't want to talk to me
About arcade rights...

284
00:22:43.655 --> 00:22:47.659
until I pay them for the rights
for the computer games.

285
00:22:47.784 --> 00:22:51.371
And I can't do that until you pay me.

286
00:22:51.496 --> 00:22:54.833
Henk Rogers wants to talk to Kevin Maxwell.
- What is he doing here?

287
00:22:54.958 --> 00:22:57.044
Let him in.
- Why?

288
00:22:57.586 --> 00:22:59.505
Then I'll just.
- Sit.

289
00:23:00.088 --> 00:23:03.133
We form a unified whole.
Got it?

290
00:23:04.927 --> 00:23:10.307
Mr. Rogers. What a nice surprise.
Robert Maxwell. of Mirror Group.

291
00:23:11.099 --> 00:23:12.809
Wow. Hi.

292
00:23:13.852 --> 00:23:18.065
If I'm disturbing you. I can...
- Well. no. We were just talking about Tetris.

293
00:23:18.190 --> 00:23:21.068
Robert Stein of Andromeda Software.
And my son...

294
00:23:21.193 --> 00:23:23.779
I can introduce myself. father. Thank you.

295
00:23:23.904 --> 00:23:28.909
Kevin Maxwell. Director of Mirrorsoft.
- We spoke.

296
00:23:30.118 --> 00:23:32.871
By phone.
You sold my arcade rights to Sega.

297
00:23:33.455 --> 00:23:35.624
Well. that worked out well. didn't it?

298
00:23:37.501 --> 00:23:41.880
Before I forget: this is
for the Russians. according to my contract.

299
00:23:42.005 --> 00:23:44.925
A video of the Japanese Tetris.

300
00:23:45.425 --> 00:23:50.806
We appreciate
your bringing it yourself. Mr. Rogers....

301
00:23:50.931 --> 00:23:53.642
but you could have
just sent it.

302
00:23:53.767 --> 00:23:58.439
Yeah. but then I wouldn't have
been able to talk to you about portable Tetris.

303
00:23:58.564 --> 00:23:59.857
Portable?

304
00:24:02.234 --> 00:24:05.153
I just don't know
who controls the rights for that.

305
00:24:06.071 --> 00:24:07.291
U?

306
00:24:08.740 --> 00:24:09.960
Without a doubt.

307
00:24:11.410 --> 00:24:12.619
Yes.

308
00:24:12.744 --> 00:24:17.166
Mr. Stein controls all
exclusive worldwide licensing rights.

309
00:24:17.291 --> 00:24:22.129
So arcades. game consoles.
computers and portable devices.

310
00:24:22.254 --> 00:24:25.549
We license everything through him.
- Fantastic.

311
00:24:26.466 --> 00:24:30.804
Then I want to buy the worldwide rights
to buy portable devices. Today.

312
00:24:30.929 --> 00:24:33.474
Nintendo does not have a portable device.

313
00:24:33.599 --> 00:24:36.810
Why would they have the rights...
- I can't say anything about that.

314
00:24:36.935 --> 00:24:40.314
But I may make on their behalf
make a very generous offer.

315
00:24:40.439 --> 00:24:43.901
We will consider your offer.
- I will take care of this. father.

316
00:24:45.068 --> 00:24:47.029
We will consider your offer.

317
00:24:48.197 --> 00:24:51.241
I haven't said anything yet.
- Indeed.

318
00:24:54.369 --> 00:24:56.330
Have fun still in London.

319
00:25:03.170 --> 00:25:04.390
Goodbye.

320
00:25:07.216 --> 00:25:08.717
You can go. Mr. Stein.

321
00:25:08.842 --> 00:25:11.678
And don't come back
without signed contracts.

322
00:25:11.803 --> 00:25:14.556
Also for portable Tetris. Got it?

323
00:25:24.024 --> 00:25:25.651
We have to pay the Russians.

324
00:25:25.776 --> 00:25:28.570
The Russians don't care about money. kid.

325
00:25:28.695 --> 00:25:31.615
They care about loyalty.
Prime Minister Gorbachev is a friend.

326
00:25:31.740 --> 00:25:33.951
We are publishing his memoirs. We are faithful.

327
00:25:34.076 --> 00:25:36.995
Yes. Father. our pension administrator called...

328
00:25:37.120 --> 00:25:41.375
because a few million was missing
from the workers' pension fund.

329
00:25:41.500 --> 00:25:44.503
We had to review the balance sheet
before the end of the year.

330
00:25:44.628 --> 00:25:46.755
Just a formality.
- So no problem?

331
00:25:46.880 --> 00:25:52.928
Very much not. But Kevin.
we need Tetris. understand?

332
00:26:04.982 --> 00:26:06.202
Mr. Stein.

333
00:26:06.692 --> 00:26:08.110
Mr. Stein. wait a minute.

334
00:26:08.861 --> 00:26:12.156
So what happened there?
- It's complicated.

335
00:26:12.281 --> 00:26:14.199
Do you not master portable rights?

336
00:26:14.324 --> 00:26:16.827
I didn't say that.
I said: it's complicated.

337
00:26:16.952 --> 00:26:21.665
You either master them or you don't. That's not...
- Have you ever been to Moscow?

338
00:26:21.790 --> 00:26:23.709
Ever negotiated with the Russians?

339
00:26:23.834 --> 00:26:28.088
Do you know what it's like to be in a country
where everyone is looking at you?

340
00:26:28.213 --> 00:26:32.217
No. So don't tell me
what is complicated and what is not.

341
00:26:33.010 --> 00:26:36.513
I will pay you $25.000
for the portable rights.

342
00:26:44.271 --> 00:26:46.023
Not so complicated after all. then.

343
00:26:50.569 --> 00:26:52.571
TOKIO

344
00:26:57.492 --> 00:27:00.370
Hello?
- With Howard Lincoln. Nintendo of America.

345
00:27:00.495 --> 00:27:03.791
I just heard that Robert Stein...

346
00:27:03.916 --> 00:27:08.462
sells portable Tetris to Atari
for $100.000.

347
00:27:09.588 --> 00:27:11.173
What?
- Yes. Atari.

348
00:27:11.757 --> 00:27:13.634
You know we hate those jerks.

349
00:27:13.759 --> 00:27:16.804
Now they have
a portable device with our game.

350
00:27:16.929 --> 00:27:20.057
I paid him for those rights.
- What happens?

351
00:27:20.182 --> 00:27:23.143
Will Stein let you choke
and keep the deal to himself?

352
00:27:23.268 --> 00:27:26.438
If so. he is
not only suffocate me.

353
00:27:30.150 --> 00:27:32.653
Are you selling portable Tetris to Atari?

354
00:27:32.778 --> 00:27:34.613
Kevin. Hi.
- Don't call me "Kevin.

355
00:27:34.738 --> 00:27:35.948
We are not friends.

356
00:27:36.073 --> 00:27:40.702
You trade exclusively with Mirrorsoft.
Or have you forgotten your contract?

357
00:27:41.286 --> 00:27:46.291
That contract that entitles me to
compensation for every Tetris sale?

358
00:27:46.416 --> 00:27:48.210
Because I haven't gotten anything yet.

359
00:27:50.128 --> 00:27:55.426
I don't have the portable rights yet.
but give me time.

360
00:27:55.551 --> 00:27:57.886
No. I negotiate directly with the Russians.

361
00:27:58.554 --> 00:27:59.847
We are ready.

362
00:28:01.932 --> 00:28:04.434
Ready?
- Ready.

363
00:28:05.477 --> 00:28:07.354
I don't care. I'm going to Moscow.

364
00:28:07.479 --> 00:28:10.357
Wait.
You can't just go to the Soviet Union.

365
00:28:10.482 --> 00:28:13.861
You need a business visa
and approval needed. Months of work.

366
00:28:13.986 --> 00:28:15.779
I am arranging a tourist visa.

367
00:28:15.904 --> 00:28:19.074
Lying? That's a felony.
Then they can lock you up.

368
00:28:19.199 --> 00:28:21.660
I'll risk it.
- Who are you going to talk to?

369
00:28:23.161 --> 00:28:25.748
A company called ELORG.

370
00:28:25.873 --> 00:28:29.710
You don't have companies there.
They probably belong to the KGB.

371
00:28:29.835 --> 00:28:32.046
Do you guys want that game?
- Yes.

372
00:28:32.171 --> 00:28:34.131
But you want to enter a communist country....

373
00:28:34.256 --> 00:28:37.259
that America still
sees as their greatest enemy.

374
00:28:37.384 --> 00:28:39.845
If you go.
we can't protect you.

375
00:28:43.557 --> 00:28:45.475
Where are you going?

376
00:28:50.147 --> 00:28:51.648
MOSKOU

377
00:29:00.282 --> 00:29:03.076
You are Danish?
- No. Dutch.

378
00:29:03.660 --> 00:29:05.204
You sound American.

379
00:29:05.329 --> 00:29:08.248
I grew up in New York.
but I'm Dutch.

380
00:29:09.666 --> 00:29:11.251
And I live in Japan.

381
00:29:44.284 --> 00:29:46.453
Interpreter?
- No. thank you.

382
00:29:50.165 --> 00:29:51.917
Henk Rogers. Coming to report.

383
00:29:54.419 --> 00:29:56.755
Do you perhaps know where I can find ELORG?

384
00:29:56.880 --> 00:30:00.259
Also called Electronorgtechnica.
A government agency.

385
00:30:00.384 --> 00:30:02.094
The government? Nyet.

386
00:30:03.595 --> 00:30:06.431
'No' as in: you don't know.
or as in: you want...

387
00:30:18.318 --> 00:30:19.820
There is a visitor.

388
00:30:24.116 --> 00:30:26.201
ELORG. Phone number?

389
00:30:31.790 --> 00:30:33.876
Need an interpreter?
- No. thanks.

390
00:30:34.626 --> 00:30:35.961
Interpreter.
- Thank you.

391
00:30:43.468 --> 00:30:44.688
Cab.

392
00:30:46.305 --> 00:30:47.525
Cab.

393
00:30:53.020 --> 00:30:55.939
All the fish and meat are gone.

394
00:30:56.732 --> 00:31:00.819
Please. You must have something more.
My family is hungry.

395
00:31:01.236 --> 00:31:02.738
I have money.

396
00:31:08.410 --> 00:31:11.038
Take this.
- No. You also have a family.

397
00:31:11.830 --> 00:31:14.666
My family will manage.
- Thank you.

398
00:31:20.130 --> 00:31:21.632
Greetings.

399
00:31:23.258 --> 00:31:25.052
Would you like an escort?

400
00:31:26.428 --> 00:31:27.763
Excuse me?

401
00:31:28.764 --> 00:31:33.185
Escort; noun.
Helper in difficult situations.

402
00:31:34.144 --> 00:31:39.399
Synonym for companion.
Sasha. Interpreter. Pleased to meet you.

403
00:31:41.026 --> 00:31:42.403
Do you want history?

404
00:31:42.528 --> 00:31:46.782
We can go to Stalin's Seven Sisters.
his palaces for the proletariat.

405
00:31:47.282 --> 00:31:50.285
Or art?
We can go to the Pushkin Museum.

406
00:31:50.410 --> 00:31:55.916
Actually. I would especially like to go to ELORG.

407
00:31:57.668 --> 00:32:00.796
I thought you were here on vacation.

408
00:32:01.421 --> 00:32:02.756
So you know it?

409
00:32:18.105 --> 00:32:21.108
Mr. Rogers. you are not in America.

410
00:32:21.733 --> 00:32:25.779
Entering a government building without
invitation is strictly prohibited.

411
00:32:25.904 --> 00:32:31.451
I traveled 7.500 kilometers for this.
I won't let a door stop me.

412
00:32:33.745 --> 00:32:35.038
Papers?

413
00:32:42.129 --> 00:32:44.298
Nikolai Yevgenyevich...
- Yes?

414
00:32:44.464 --> 00:32:46.258
Someone is there for you.

415
00:32:48.927 --> 00:32:50.220
I am listening.

416
00:32:51.388 --> 00:32:53.932
Yes. Hi. Henk Rogers.

417
00:32:56.935 --> 00:32:58.395
From Bullet-Proof Software.

418
00:32:59.730 --> 00:33:05.319
I'm releasing the game console version
of Tetris out in Japan....

419
00:33:05.444 --> 00:33:08.405
and I want the license
for the portable version.

420
00:33:09.072 --> 00:33:10.292
What is that?

421
00:33:11.241 --> 00:33:15.287
Where does it come from?
- Sorry. I don't speak...

422
00:33:17.164 --> 00:33:18.457
Moments.

423
00:33:18.957 --> 00:33:21.126
Sorry. Sasha. but I need you.

424
00:33:22.711 --> 00:33:24.046
Everything will be fine.

425
00:33:26.340 --> 00:33:31.845
This is Sasha. my interpreter.
- Hello. my name is Sasha. I am an interpreter.

426
00:33:34.848 --> 00:33:36.141
I'm Henk Rogers.

427
00:33:37.184 --> 00:33:39.895
I'm releasing Tetris
for Nintendo in Japan.

428
00:33:46.109 --> 00:33:48.570
He asks. "What is Nintendo?

429
00:33:49.071 --> 00:33:50.948
Ha. Funny.

430
00:33:53.867 --> 00:33:56.787
Nintendo is
the most popular game console in the world.

431
00:34:02.084 --> 00:34:06.296
ELORG has never given anyone
licensed game consoles.

432
00:34:07.673 --> 00:34:10.259
Computer only.

433
00:34:11.342 --> 00:34:12.886
That can't be right. Look...

434
00:34:14.221 --> 00:34:18.141
ELORG has sold the license
to Robert Stein of Andromeda.

435
00:34:18.641 --> 00:34:20.601
And Andromeda to Mirrorsoft.

436
00:34:20.726 --> 00:34:25.107
And Mirrorsoft's representative in
Las Vegas again to Bullet-Proof Software.

437
00:34:25.232 --> 00:34:26.452
And that's me.

438
00:34:28.985 --> 00:34:30.696
Mirrorsoft had to send it in.

439
00:34:35.033 --> 00:34:37.411
He did not get a bond.

440
00:34:39.830 --> 00:34:42.791
And this is an illegal copy.

441
00:34:44.793 --> 00:34:46.335
We'd better get going.

442
00:34:47.795 --> 00:34:50.924
Does he think I stole Tetris?
- Correct.

443
00:34:51.507 --> 00:34:56.346
Say I have my whole life
invested in this game.

444
00:34:56.471 --> 00:34:57.691
He is mistaken.

445
00:35:01.727 --> 00:35:04.563
Get out of this government building soon.

446
00:35:04.688 --> 00:35:09.860
Otherwise. your tourist visa will send you to
prison as a fraudster and intruder.

447
00:35:11.320 --> 00:35:15.616
He is not mistaken. he said.
- Is that all he said?

448
00:35:17.242 --> 00:35:18.462
Yes.

449
00:35:19.077 --> 00:35:22.122
Okay. Say I want to set the record straight.

450
00:35:22.623 --> 00:35:25.125
We arrange the game console rights....

451
00:35:26.585 --> 00:35:28.921
and then the portable rights.

452
00:35:36.094 --> 00:35:38.347
Come back tomorrow at 9 a.m.

453
00:35:38.472 --> 00:35:41.266
But I warn you...
- Okay. Great. Thank you.

454
00:35:41.850 --> 00:35:43.070
Thank you.

455
00:35:45.103 --> 00:35:47.564
You're going to... Okay. Thank you.

456
00:35:52.986 --> 00:35:55.155
Now "an international phone booth.

457
00:35:55.948 --> 00:36:00.077
International telephone booths
don't exist in the Soviet Union. Henk.

458
00:36:00.202 --> 00:36:01.870
I have to call home.

459
00:36:02.955 --> 00:36:05.958
You don't get it.
We put our house on the line....

460
00:36:06.083 --> 00:36:09.753
For the game console rights for Tetris.
And now I don't have them?

461
00:36:10.838 --> 00:36:13.465
If I don't take care of this. I'm screwed.

462
00:36:16.134 --> 00:36:19.847
Your hotel has telephones.
- Okay. Good. Come with me.

463
00:36:19.972 --> 00:36:24.852
But you will have to wait. Only
a few connections out of our beautiful country.

464
00:36:24.977 --> 00:36:26.197
How long?

465
00:36:26.812 --> 00:36:30.816
Between eight hours and a week.
- What?

466
00:36:32.192 --> 00:36:36.155
Okay. but they do have
a fax machine at the hotel. right?

467
00:36:36.280 --> 00:36:40.242
Faxes and telexes are
only in government buildings. Henk.

468
00:36:40.367 --> 00:36:44.663
Mr. Rogers. may I speak to you. please?

469
00:36:58.719 --> 00:37:00.179
Do you know who I am?

470
00:37:02.055 --> 00:37:05.100
I do have an inkling.
- Nice.

471
00:37:06.810 --> 00:37:09.063
I assume your interpreter told you....

472
00:37:09.188 --> 00:37:14.151
That foreigners may not enter
be allowed to enter a government building.

473
00:37:15.777 --> 00:37:18.447
Go home. Got it?

474
00:37:34.713 --> 00:37:37.716
Mr. Maxwell. Valentin Trifonov...

475
00:37:37.841 --> 00:37:41.053
Of the Central Committee.
Foreign Trade Department.

476
00:37:41.178 --> 00:37:45.057
Welcome to Russia.
- My father said Gorbachev was coming.

477
00:37:46.475 --> 00:37:50.187
You are not Gorbachev.
- And you are not your father.

478
00:37:52.105 --> 00:37:53.482
You are coming for Tetris?

479
00:37:57.277 --> 00:38:00.155
We'll see what we can arrange.

480
00:38:11.750 --> 00:38:12.793
Morning. Sasha.

481
00:38:12.918 --> 00:38:16.004
Can I possibly
change your mind?

482
00:38:16.129 --> 00:38:17.422
Forget it.

483
00:38:19.758 --> 00:38:20.978
Ready?

484
00:38:28.642 --> 00:38:33.230
This is Aleksey Pazhitnov.
the creator of Tetris.

485
00:38:33.355 --> 00:38:35.524
Wow. really?
- Mr. Rogers...

486
00:38:36.733 --> 00:38:40.445
Mr. Belikov wants you to understand
that he does not trust you.

487
00:38:42.865 --> 00:38:48.287
U... Sorry. these are not my
words. You are a lying thief.

488
00:38:51.081 --> 00:38:52.374
And a terrible cook.

489
00:38:57.004 --> 00:38:58.797
That was a joke.

490
00:38:59.506 --> 00:39:01.758
He doesn't understand.
- I see.

491
00:39:07.014 --> 00:39:08.599
Go on. Mr. Belikov.

492
00:39:13.854 --> 00:39:17.232
Excuse me. who are you?
- Please take a seat.

493
00:39:20.819 --> 00:39:25.991
A more important question is:
who are you. Henk Rogers?

494
00:39:29.161 --> 00:39:33.332
According to your visa. you are a tourist.
You are not. A crime.

495
00:39:33.457 --> 00:39:37.836
It says on yourTetris game
That you have the license. You don't.

496
00:39:37.961 --> 00:39:40.255
Another crime.

497
00:39:41.340 --> 00:39:44.718
So this is my proposal.

498
00:39:46.011 --> 00:39:51.934
You go home and stop the production
of Tetris. Then there is no problem.

499
00:39:52.935 --> 00:39:55.270
If you stay here. there are consequences.

500
00:39:58.273 --> 00:40:01.276
I'm not going home without a deal.

501
00:40:02.653 --> 00:40:03.612
Sorry.

502
00:40:03.737 --> 00:40:07.783
'Sorry' won't save you
in our courts. Mr. Rogers.

503
00:40:09.284 --> 00:40:10.869
Mr. Belikov.

504
00:40:27.845 --> 00:40:29.065
Aleksej.

505
00:40:30.764 --> 00:40:33.058
I wanted to say that your game is great.

506
00:40:34.768 --> 00:40:36.770
Thank you. I speak English.

507
00:40:37.521 --> 00:40:39.356
And I have so many questions.

508
00:40:39.481 --> 00:40:42.985
But first I want to say:
once I resolve this misunderstanding....

509
00:40:43.110 --> 00:40:45.821
and hopefully get the portable rights

510
00:40:47.406 --> 00:40:48.949
I'll make you rich.

511
00:40:50.868 --> 00:40:53.829
Mr. Rogers...
- Please. Call me Henk.

512
00:40:56.665 --> 00:41:02.629
Mr Rogers. I have no right
to make money off my game.

513
00:41:02.754 --> 00:41:05.507
That's criminal.
- No.

514
00:41:06.258 --> 00:41:07.718
That is communism.

515
00:41:11.096 --> 00:41:14.141
If that sucker is a thief.
then lock him up.

516
00:41:16.351 --> 00:41:18.228
Are the other buyers there?

517
00:41:21.023 --> 00:41:22.524
Keep them separate.

518
00:41:22.858 --> 00:41:26.278
We'll give those capitalists
a taste of their own medicine.

519
00:41:30.657 --> 00:41:35.621
If I were a thief. why
would I come to show my game?

520
00:41:43.295 --> 00:41:45.798
Because you want the portable rights.

521
00:41:45.923 --> 00:41:49.301
If I had stolen
and arcade rights had been stolen...

522
00:41:49.426 --> 00:41:51.929
why not the portable rights then?

523
00:41:57.184 --> 00:42:00.854
Mr. Belikov asks
Why you start talking about arcade rights.

524
00:42:00.979 --> 00:42:03.524
I also
bought the Japanese arcade rights...

525
00:42:03.649 --> 00:42:07.361
and then heard that Mirrorsoft
had already sold them to Sega.

526
00:42:07.486 --> 00:42:08.779
Stop. stop. stop.

527
00:42:16.328 --> 00:42:20.457
ELORG has never sold anyone
sold the arcade rights. Henk.

528
00:42:23.502 --> 00:42:24.722
Wait a minute.

529
00:42:25.212 --> 00:42:30.384
So you mean you only sold the rights for
Tetris on the computer?

530
00:42:33.887 --> 00:42:35.347
May I see the contract?

531
00:42:37.307 --> 00:42:40.102
Please. Then I will understand it better.

532
00:42:41.395 --> 00:42:43.397
I don't know if you know....

533
00:42:44.064 --> 00:42:45.816
but Stein and Mirrorsoft...

534
00:42:45.941 --> 00:42:51.029
are selling the game console
and arcade rights for Tetris worldwide.

535
00:43:15.179 --> 00:43:16.513
Mr. Belikov?

536
00:43:17.890 --> 00:43:20.100
I'm Robert Stein.

537
00:43:20.726 --> 00:43:24.855
I come for the contracts
for arcade and portable rights.

538
00:43:24.980 --> 00:43:28.233
Mr. Stein. a moment.
- Hm? What?

539
00:43:31.445 --> 00:43:34.072
Mr. Belikov. How nice that you could come.

540
00:43:35.365 --> 00:43:37.493
Mr. Belikov asks. "What is this?

541
00:43:37.618 --> 00:43:41.080
That looks like Tetris
for the Nintendo in Japan.

542
00:43:41.205 --> 00:43:44.458
I come for the portable rights.
not for that.

543
00:43:48.754 --> 00:43:53.258
Did you sell Tetris games
sold to Henk Rogers?

544
00:43:53.383 --> 00:43:56.261
I run one of
the largest media companies in Europe.

545
00:43:56.386 --> 00:43:59.515
I don't concern myself with trifles.

546
00:44:01.683 --> 00:44:07.147
You're saying you don't know this game?
- No. I'm saying I want to get to the point.

547
00:44:08.690 --> 00:44:11.735
Do you think it's illegal?
- Well. maybe?

548
00:44:12.319 --> 00:44:14.154
Can we talk about portable Tetris?

549
00:44:15.322 --> 00:44:17.866
Tomorrow. please.
- Yes.

550
00:44:18.367 --> 00:44:20.327
Rotten communists.

551
00:44:24.998 --> 00:44:29.127
Okay. I read it. and you are right.

552
00:44:29.628 --> 00:44:33.340
You did not knowingly sell Robert Stein
sold the game console rights.

553
00:44:35.217 --> 00:44:36.552
But here's the thing.

554
00:44:41.807 --> 00:44:44.518
Okay. this is a Nintendo.

555
00:44:46.395 --> 00:44:49.022
And this is a personal computer.

556
00:44:50.274 --> 00:44:51.567
What is the difference?

557
00:44:53.277 --> 00:44:54.987
No keyboard with the Nintendo.

558
00:44:56.196 --> 00:44:57.739
No keyboard at the...

559
00:44:58.907 --> 00:45:00.158
You speak English?

560
00:45:01.285 --> 00:45:04.329
Yes. of course. Listen. I'm sorry.

561
00:45:05.247 --> 00:45:08.458
Robert Stein screwed you over.
But legally...

562
00:45:09.126 --> 00:45:12.880
he didn't rob you.
and so I didn't either.

563
00:45:15.591 --> 00:45:18.677
Next time
you should define "computer" better.

564
00:45:27.227 --> 00:45:31.065
And arcade rights?
- There's nothing about that in that contract.

565
00:45:31.190 --> 00:45:32.316
MUNT INSERT

566
00:45:32.441 --> 00:45:34.359
Stein did steal that one.

567
00:45:35.319 --> 00:45:36.612
What are those worth?

568
00:45:37.613 --> 00:45:39.489
$150.000.

569
00:45:44.661 --> 00:45:46.079
Where does he keep going?

570
00:45:46.830 --> 00:45:48.050
Mr. Belikov.

571
00:45:49.374 --> 00:45:51.418
Mr. Belikov.
- No.

572
00:45:54.880 --> 00:45:57.966
Aleksej. we started out wrong.

573
00:45:58.091 --> 00:46:03.138
Would you like to go out to dinner sometime?
- Mr. Rogers. I'm not for sale.

574
00:46:07.684 --> 00:46:13.190
Is article 40
a more careful definition of "personal computer"?

575
00:46:14.233 --> 00:46:18.320
'A personal computer consists of a processor.
monitor. hard drive and keyboard.'

576
00:46:18.445 --> 00:46:19.905
Yes. much better.
- Keyboard.

577
00:46:20.030 --> 00:46:23.492
But this was signed years ago.
What use is that to you?

578
00:46:25.911 --> 00:46:27.704
Oh. you're welcome. you know.

579
00:46:27.829 --> 00:46:30.791
Okay. What's going on?

580
00:46:37.798 --> 00:46:40.300
What is this?
- New contract.

581
00:46:41.301 --> 00:46:46.974
$150.000 for arcade rights?
How did you come up with that amount?

582
00:46:47.099 --> 00:46:50.227
How did Sega get
the arcade rights for Tetris in Japan?

583
00:46:54.815 --> 00:46:56.035
If...

584
00:46:56.567 --> 00:47:02.364
If I sign this contract. then we can
talk about the portable rights. right?

585
00:47:04.950 --> 00:47:08.328
I need an evening
to read this contract.

586
00:47:15.544 --> 00:47:19.715
We are ready for today.
- What about the portable rights?

587
00:47:20.841 --> 00:47:24.428
That's what we're going to
bravely working on that.

588
00:47:30.142 --> 00:47:31.362
Aleksej.

589
00:47:32.352 --> 00:47:33.572
Want a ride?

590
00:47:34.813 --> 00:47:36.033
I have a car.

591
00:47:37.149 --> 00:47:38.442
Can I have a ride?

592
00:47:45.949 --> 00:47:47.284
Where are you from?

593
00:47:49.703 --> 00:47:51.830
I am Dutch. raised in New York.

594
00:47:52.414 --> 00:47:56.376
My parents were Dutch
with Jewish and Indonesian ancestors.

595
00:47:58.337 --> 00:48:00.631
I'm kind of like Eddie Van Halen.

596
00:48:03.217 --> 00:48:05.344
I have no need to chat.

597
00:48:08.138 --> 00:48:11.225
Believe it or not.
but I really want to get to know you.

598
00:48:12.017 --> 00:48:15.020
Not only as a business partner.
but also as a fan.

599
00:48:17.814 --> 00:48:19.733
Come eat at my hotel tonight.

600
00:48:20.651 --> 00:48:21.871
No.

601
00:48:22.778 --> 00:48:24.780
Can I visit you then?

602
00:48:27.866 --> 00:48:32.162
Having a foreigner visit
is a crime here.

603
00:48:33.288 --> 00:48:34.748
So.

604
00:48:37.167 --> 00:48:39.461
just call.

605
00:48:41.672 --> 00:48:42.892
Great.

606
00:48:43.423 --> 00:48:44.800
Thanks for the elevator.

607
00:48:45.551 --> 00:48:48.262
Do you know how long my conversation was?
- About two minutes.

608
00:48:48.387 --> 00:48:50.848
Sir. you need to learn better manners.

609
00:48:52.099 --> 00:48:56.478
You say you don't know this game?
- No. I'm saying I'm on point....

610
00:48:57.396 --> 00:48:58.647
Are you spying on me?

611
00:48:59.189 --> 00:49:03.402
Asshole.
- Take care. Kevin.

612
00:49:07.072 --> 00:49:11.368
Let's go for a walk. Outside. All right?

613
00:49:30.345 --> 00:49:32.514
6 ROSTOVSKAYA PEREVLOK.
7:00 PM.

614
00:49:34.725 --> 00:49:36.643
What are you offering for Tetris?

615
00:49:36.768 --> 00:49:39.438
Exclusive publication rights for...

616
00:49:39.563 --> 00:49:42.107
No. How much money?

617
00:49:42.941 --> 00:49:46.570
Those rights are worth two million
dollars worth. A fair exchange. in other words.

618
00:49:47.821 --> 00:49:51.116
Fair exchange. my lair.
- I beg your pardon?

619
00:49:52.117 --> 00:49:53.744
This is Russia. dammit.

620
00:49:54.578 --> 00:49:56.663
You don't think money is important.

621
00:49:59.625 --> 00:50:02.336
Where are you from?
- What difference does that make?

622
00:50:02.461 --> 00:50:05.005
I myself come from the kraj Stavropol.

623
00:50:06.006 --> 00:50:09.843
My parents were kolkhozes.
You know. Share builders.

624
00:50:10.719 --> 00:50:14.306
They worked 18 hours a day
on a state farm.

625
00:50:14.431 --> 00:50:16.725
The government took everything away from them.

626
00:50:16.850 --> 00:50:20.646
I understood at a very young age:
to be successful in this society....

627
00:50:20.771 --> 00:50:24.066
I needed this. And nothing else.

628
00:50:25.067 --> 00:50:28.695
I didn't get where I am
By other people's help. like you.

629
00:50:28.820 --> 00:50:31.323
So spare me the Bolshevik bullshit.

630
00:50:34.785 --> 00:50:38.205
Communism is dying out.
Soon I will lose my job.

631
00:50:38.830 --> 00:50:42.751
Like you. I want the best deal.

632
00:50:43.794 --> 00:50:45.420
You want bribes?

633
00:50:46.880 --> 00:50:48.131
Is that what you mean?

634
00:50:50.175 --> 00:50:52.761
No. I run an honest business.

635
00:50:52.886 --> 00:50:56.515
No one becomes a billionaire
by staying honest. Mr. Maxwell.

636
00:50:56.640 --> 00:50:59.351
Nor
by trusting corrupt politicians.

637
00:50:59.476 --> 00:51:03.438
If you are looking for a pawn.
you better fuck off.

638
00:51:04.982 --> 00:51:06.202
Have a great day.

639
00:51:10.153 --> 00:51:14.908
100.000 American dollars.
if I get the deal.

640
00:51:15.033 --> 00:51:18.370
No. I'm not asking that.

641
00:51:19.162 --> 00:51:21.456
Boris.
- Stop recording.

642
00:51:24.209 --> 00:51:25.711
800.000.

643
00:51:25.836 --> 00:51:28.422
Half as an advance.
into a Swiss account.

644
00:51:28.547 --> 00:51:32.426
300. and I'll pay
when I have the portable rights.

645
00:51:32.551 --> 00:51:36.555
I will talk to Mr. Rogers. though.
- Henk Rogers has no money.

646
00:51:36.680 --> 00:51:39.558
He works for Nintendo.
and they don't bribe you.

647
00:51:39.683 --> 00:51:43.520
And Robert Stein is too stingy.
so you don't have to threaten him either.

648
00:51:43.645 --> 00:51:46.231
400. Last bid.

649
00:51:47.941 --> 00:51:49.443
Well then.

650
00:51:49.568 --> 00:51:51.153
And Mr. Trifonov?

651
00:51:51.278 --> 00:51:55.699
Kevin doesn't need to know any of this.

652
00:52:20.933 --> 00:52:24.561
Why are we doing this?
You know what happened to your father.

653
00:52:24.728 --> 00:52:27.022
Ever said "no" to an American?

654
00:52:28.398 --> 00:52:29.618
This is meaningless.

655
00:52:38.700 --> 00:52:40.327
Hello.

656
00:52:40.452 --> 00:52:41.412
Hi.

657
00:52:41.537 --> 00:52:43.997
This is Maya. She is ten.

658
00:52:45.123 --> 00:52:46.542
Julie is eight.

659
00:52:47.918 --> 00:52:53.340
Michael. six. Leo is three.
And this is my wife. Akemi.

660
00:52:54.174 --> 00:52:56.260
Met as a student. in Hawaii.

661
00:52:56.385 --> 00:52:59.888
We fell in love
and I went with her to Tokyo.

662
00:53:00.472 --> 00:53:02.266
You have lived in many places.

663
00:53:03.433 --> 00:53:04.653
Yes. actually. it did.

664
00:53:05.602 --> 00:53:08.564
What about you?
- I only lived here.

665
00:53:08.689 --> 00:53:11.775
In Moscow?
- In this apartment.

666
00:53:17.948 --> 00:53:22.202
So. Henk. what do you think of Moscow?
- If I'm being honest?

667
00:53:23.287 --> 00:53:24.872
A little confusing. though.

668
00:53:24.997 --> 00:53:28.500
Russia is a country
that you must learn to love.

669
00:53:28.625 --> 00:53:32.212
Like our literature
is cold and dark on the outside.

670
00:53:33.005 --> 00:53:37.801
But also romantic and animated.
- No one sees that side anymore.

671
00:53:38.427 --> 00:53:40.554
How did you discover Tetris. Henk?

672
00:53:41.513 --> 00:53:46.226
I was at the Electronics Fair in Las Vegas
to sell a game of mine.

673
00:53:46.351 --> 00:53:48.604
Then I saw your husband's....

674
00:53:48.729 --> 00:53:50.439
And picked it.
- Nina.

675
00:53:51.023 --> 00:53:56.445
No. that doesn't matter. I bought it
from a big company that lied to me.

676
00:53:58.697 --> 00:54:02.409
But I want to set the record straight. Because Tetris...

677
00:54:03.785 --> 00:54:05.037
Is just so good.

678
00:54:09.416 --> 00:54:11.460
He is stupid. but honest.

679
00:54:14.588 --> 00:54:18.550
So you design games. Henk?

680
00:54:19.885 --> 00:54:21.053
And I'm a programmer.

681
00:54:21.178 --> 00:54:24.306
Well. lately
I've been doing mostly sales.

682
00:54:24.431 --> 00:54:27.309
Pascal or assembly language?

683
00:54:27.434 --> 00:54:29.186
That's what I wanted to ask you.

684
00:54:30.729 --> 00:54:33.899
I like Pascal.
but mostly work with assembly language.

685
00:54:34.024 --> 00:54:37.152
Never underestimate...
- The power of BASIC.

686
00:54:41.490 --> 00:54:42.908
That was creepy.

687
00:54:48.747 --> 00:54:49.967
Is this it?

688
00:54:50.791 --> 00:54:52.011
The original?

689
00:54:59.550 --> 00:55:01.176
Unbelievable.

690
00:55:05.973 --> 00:55:07.391
May I play sometime?

691
00:55:19.736 --> 00:55:23.991
I don't get this.
Why do multiple rows never disappear?

692
00:55:24.491 --> 00:55:25.711
Because.

693
00:55:27.411 --> 00:55:29.037
I never thought about that.

694
00:55:30.622 --> 00:55:33.250
We should make four rows
should disappear.

695
00:55:33.792 --> 00:55:35.210
"We?

696
00:55:36.128 --> 00:55:40.632
What. yes.
Give it a try. It can't hurt.

697
00:55:44.761 --> 00:55:46.847
Henk?

698
00:55:54.563 --> 00:55:58.275
A higher level means more points.
so you... Sorry.

699
00:56:06.491 --> 00:56:09.578
Almost. But we need something more.

700
00:56:19.087 --> 00:56:22.674
Life is hard. We deserve
To celebrate little things.

701
00:56:22.799 --> 00:56:24.718
I had forgotten how much fun this is.

702
00:56:29.223 --> 00:56:30.443
What?

703
00:56:32.976 --> 00:56:36.021
Away. Be still. Come.

704
00:56:37.689 --> 00:56:40.108
Be still. Quiet.

705
00:56:50.702 --> 00:56:54.206
Good evening. Do you have any salt?
- Salt?

706
00:56:59.586 --> 00:57:02.214
The neighbor.
- Aleksey. please.

707
00:57:07.094 --> 00:57:09.763
What...
- Sorry. Henk. You have to go.

708
00:57:09.888 --> 00:57:13.934
Okay. But only if you come with me.
- What?

709
00:57:14.059 --> 00:57:16.770
We go out once.
But not to a tourist bar.

710
00:57:16.895 --> 00:57:21.442
Show me your side of Moscow.
- Henk. that's not a good idea.

711
00:57:21.567 --> 00:57:24.778
Yes. but sometimes
you have to have flack for the rules.

712
00:57:24.903 --> 00:57:26.655
That is why I am in Moscow.

713
00:57:26.780 --> 00:57:30.784
And I think that's why you invited me
invited me here tonight.

714
00:57:35.497 --> 00:57:39.626
Here it is.
You had something like that in mind. didn't you. Henk?

715
00:57:43.172 --> 00:57:44.298
Thank you.

716
00:57:44.423 --> 00:57:47.509
Thank you. Thank you very much. Thank you.

717
00:57:48.468 --> 00:57:49.688
Pros.

718
00:57:50.345 --> 00:57:53.974
Do you know these people?
- There are colleagues of mine among them. yes.

719
00:57:54.600 --> 00:57:55.559
Great music.

720
00:57:55.684 --> 00:58:01.815
Well. I myself prefer Mozart
or Russian folk songs.

721
00:58:01.940 --> 00:58:03.160
And not. um...

722
00:58:11.158 --> 00:58:12.701
What did she say?
- "People.

723
00:58:14.286 --> 00:58:16.413
News from the Baltics.

724
00:58:18.582 --> 00:58:23.462
The Estonians are protesting. They demand
independence from the Soviet Union.

725
00:58:25.422 --> 00:58:30.469
We are all
fed up with hypocrisy and professional politicians.

726
00:58:31.303 --> 00:58:33.055
We want freedom.

727
00:58:34.723 --> 00:58:36.225
Freedom of speech.

728
00:58:36.725 --> 00:58:38.810
Freedom of art and expression.

729
00:58:42.731 --> 00:58:44.316
We want Coca-Cola.

730
00:58:48.820 --> 00:58:50.948
And jeans from Levi's.

731
00:58:52.115 --> 00:58:53.825
To this we drink.

732
00:59:02.125 --> 00:59:03.418
Great song.

733
00:59:21.812 --> 00:59:24.982
They know the text.
- Good ideas know no bounds.

734
00:59:32.281 --> 00:59:33.782
Sing along.
- No. no. no.

735
00:59:34.408 --> 00:59:37.369
Come on. Please?
- I don't sing. No.

736
01:00:17.910 --> 01:00:20.078
Come on. How can you still hold back?

737
01:00:30.130 --> 01:00:31.423
Aleksej.

738
01:00:36.637 --> 01:00:38.972
You see. we are not that different.

739
01:00:40.891 --> 01:00:44.645
Thank you for showing me this.
I'm glad for that.

740
01:00:53.445 --> 01:00:54.821
We go home. Cleaning up.

741
01:01:05.707 --> 01:01:07.751
Akemi Rogers?

742
01:01:08.335 --> 01:01:11.213
We are from
the Russian embassy in Tokyo.

743
01:01:11.338 --> 01:01:13.048
Who let you in?

744
01:01:14.091 --> 01:01:15.884
Do you know where your husband is?

745
01:01:16.760 --> 01:01:18.554
Did your husband call you?

746
01:01:40.492 --> 01:01:44.997
If he calls. just tell him
that he needs to come home.

747
01:01:46.540 --> 01:01:47.833
Immediately.

748
01:01:52.171 --> 01:01:53.391
You have beautiful children.

749
01:01:59.636 --> 01:02:00.856
Go home.

750
01:02:02.431 --> 01:02:04.516
And thanks for the Levi's.

751
01:02:07.811 --> 01:02:09.897
Interpreter?
- No. thank you.

752
01:02:29.208 --> 01:02:30.959
What the hell...

753
01:02:38.592 --> 01:02:39.812
Henk.

754
01:02:40.427 --> 01:02:42.971
Thank God. you're fine.

755
01:02:46.892 --> 01:02:49.228
They also searched my apartment.

756
01:02:49.353 --> 01:02:53.899
But I don't get it. I want to help.
Why do they feel so threatened?

757
01:02:56.235 --> 01:03:00.197
You are a foreigner
and want to buy Russian property.

758
01:03:00.948 --> 01:03:03.992
For many people
that is practically treason.

759
01:03:04.117 --> 01:03:05.619
It's just a game.

760
01:03:06.286 --> 01:03:07.621
For you. yes.

761
01:03:07.746 --> 01:03:11.458
But those in power see that
as a first step.

762
01:03:11.583 --> 01:03:15.712
If they allow this. they think
that soon all of Russia will be for sale.

763
01:03:17.589 --> 01:03:22.261
Henk. don't sacrifice everything for this.

764
01:03:29.935 --> 01:03:32.062
I am married.

765
01:03:33.814 --> 01:03:35.034
I didn't want to...

766
01:03:40.362 --> 01:03:41.582
You just have to go.

767
01:03:49.997 --> 01:03:53.166
Good morning. Peter and Dmitri.

768
01:03:53.917 --> 01:03:55.711
Tennis champions.

769
01:03:56.545 --> 01:04:00.048
Are you going to school?
What a good daddy you have.

770
01:04:00.549 --> 01:04:04.469
That he brings you so early
Whereas yesterday he was up so late.

771
01:04:05.012 --> 01:04:10.559
Daddy. who is that?
- English? Impressive.

772
01:04:11.101 --> 01:04:13.896
Your mother is an English teacher. isn't she?

773
01:04:14.396 --> 01:04:17.983
Well. that's a good job.
Reliable income.

774
01:04:19.401 --> 01:04:23.822
Did dad ever tell you
what happened to his father?

775
01:04:25.199 --> 01:04:28.285
No. He should do that then.

776
01:04:28.410 --> 01:04:33.457
Because you know. history
can sometimes just repeat itself.

777
01:04:45.552 --> 01:04:49.681
Mr. Rogers? The international phone
is ready. Three minutes.

778
01:04:51.308 --> 01:04:57.064
Come on. come on. Pick up.
- Hello?

779
01:04:57.981 --> 01:05:00.317
Maya. With Dad.

780
01:05:00.776 --> 01:05:02.277
Are you coming home?

781
01:05:02.402 --> 01:05:05.989
My school concert is soon.
We practiced today...

782
01:05:06.114 --> 01:05:09.326
and the teacher thought
that I sounded like an angel. and....

783
01:05:10.035 --> 01:05:14.581
Maya. I promise I'll come.
but right now I need to talk to your mother.

784
01:05:14.706 --> 01:05:18.585
I also want to talk to you.
- Maya. give it to me.

785
01:05:20.420 --> 01:05:21.422
Henk?

786
01:05:21.547 --> 01:05:26.343
Hi. Call our lawyer. He needs to
fax my Mirrorsoft contract to ELORG....

787
01:05:26.468 --> 01:05:29.263
and draw up a new contract
for portable Tetris.

788
01:05:29.388 --> 01:05:35.269
I'll fill in the details.
ELORG's number is +7 495 442 481.

789
01:05:35.394 --> 01:05:37.354
Okay?
- Henk.

790
01:05:37.479 --> 01:05:40.983
There were Russians at my work.
I had to ask you to come home.

791
01:05:41.108 --> 01:05:42.328
What?

792
01:05:42.734 --> 01:05:44.319
Akemi?

793
01:05:47.114 --> 01:05:48.334
Oh. shit.

794
01:06:06.425 --> 01:06:08.135
You bastard.

795
01:06:08.260 --> 01:06:09.480
Cab.

796
01:06:10.512 --> 01:06:12.139
Cab.
- Cab.

797
01:06:17.978 --> 01:06:19.772
Why is Henk Rogers here?

798
01:06:19.897 --> 01:06:23.150
Are you trying to play us off against each other?

799
01:06:23.275 --> 01:06:25.110
If you are trying to trick me....

800
01:06:25.235 --> 01:06:28.614
Mr. Stein.
have you read your new contract?

801
01:06:28.739 --> 01:06:30.032
Yes.

802
01:06:30.574 --> 01:06:34.912
I have. It's not fair. You are charging
way too much for the arcade rights.

803
01:06:35.037 --> 01:06:40.417
And why should I re-sign
for the PC rights. which are already mine?

804
01:06:43.086 --> 01:06:46.548
I'll sign. But after that we'll talk
about portable rights. yes?

805
01:06:50.260 --> 01:06:52.221
Okay. Portable. How much?

806
01:06:52.971 --> 01:06:56.225
We will come back.
- No.

807
01:06:59.686 --> 01:07:02.981
Mr. Belikov. with all due respect.
what the hell?

808
01:07:03.941 --> 01:07:06.693
First. one of your people threatens me.

809
01:07:06.818 --> 01:07:11.240
Then you threaten my wife in Japan.
My hotel room will be trashed....

810
01:07:11.365 --> 01:07:14.326
and now I find out
that you are negotiating with Robert Stein.

811
01:07:14.451 --> 01:07:16.328
After all he has done to you?

812
01:07:16.453 --> 01:07:20.499
This doesn't make any sense.
I'm the only honest guy here.

813
01:07:21.250 --> 01:07:25.087
You are all crooks.
You only want money.

814
01:07:25.212 --> 01:07:29.299
I don't understand that. My interpreter is not here.
And where is Aleksej?

815
01:07:29.842 --> 01:07:32.177
Do you think I am the enemy here?

816
01:07:32.970 --> 01:07:35.389
I'm not.
It's not about money anymore.

817
01:07:35.514 --> 01:07:38.684
I want Aleksej to get what he deserves
and I want to show...

818
01:07:38.809 --> 01:07:42.479
That the Soviet Union is more
than missiles and military strength.

819
01:07:56.285 --> 01:07:59.496
What's that?
- Your contract with Mirrorsoft.

820
01:07:59.621 --> 01:08:05.502
That proves that I did not rob you.
And the other is my new offer.

821
01:08:05.627 --> 01:08:07.462
There are no numbers on it.

822
01:08:08.505 --> 01:08:15.512
$25.000 in advance for all portable
rights and 25 cents per copy sold.

823
01:08:16.180 --> 01:08:17.555
$25.000?

824
01:08:20.392 --> 01:08:22.227
Why so little?

825
01:08:22.810 --> 01:08:26.023
To be honest:
I have no money left.

826
01:08:27.983 --> 01:08:30.944
But the fee per copy
is very reasonable.

827
01:08:37.910 --> 01:08:40.203
How many games do you expect to sell?

828
01:08:40.328 --> 01:08:43.457
As a conservative estimate: one million.

829
01:08:44.791 --> 01:08:48.086
But actually I estimate 20 million.

830
01:08:49.671 --> 01:08:52.466
Then you get five million dollars.

831
01:08:56.678 --> 01:09:00.140
Hey. come on.
You guys are champions of cliffhangers.

832
01:09:04.228 --> 01:09:05.895
May I have a word with you?

833
01:09:08.649 --> 01:09:11.151
I have been following your negotiations.

834
01:09:11.944 --> 01:09:13.694
You did an excellent job.

835
01:09:14.321 --> 01:09:18.367
All for the Soviet Union.
Comrade Trifonov.

836
01:09:18.617 --> 01:09:19.910
Nice.

837
01:09:20.077 --> 01:09:24.247
In fact. the government has determined
that Tetris will go to Mirrorsoft.

838
01:09:31.796 --> 01:09:33.016
Good.

839
01:09:33.506 --> 01:09:34.726
Go ahead.

840
01:09:38.261 --> 01:09:40.930
Mr. Be... Oh. jeez. What is he doing here?

841
01:09:41.430 --> 01:09:44.184
Foreign trade
is my department. Mr. Maxwell.

842
01:09:45.227 --> 01:09:50.232
Okay. Mr. Belikov. Mirrorsoft is offering you
the Russian publication rights...

843
01:09:50.357 --> 01:09:53.318
For the Collier's Encyclopedia.
worth two million...

844
01:09:53.443 --> 01:09:55.988
For worldwide portable rights
for Tetris.

845
01:09:56.113 --> 01:09:58.240
And per copy?
- For heaven's sake.

846
01:09:58.365 --> 01:10:00.200
This is the deal of a lifetime.

847
01:10:06.415 --> 01:10:11.336
We are willing to make a deal with you.
Mr. Maxwell. but the times...

848
01:10:11.962 --> 01:10:13.213
Times are changing.

849
01:10:14.089 --> 01:10:16.717
We are accountable
for our choices.

850
01:10:16.842 --> 01:10:20.095
If I choose the bid without a monetary amount.
it says that...

851
01:10:20.971 --> 01:10:22.191
suspicious.

852
01:10:25.309 --> 01:10:27.394
Fine.

853
01:10:27.519 --> 01:10:29.980
All expenditures must be approved

854
01:10:30.105 --> 01:10:34.443
but unofficially I'm offering ELORG
a million. by the end of the week.

855
01:10:35.485 --> 01:10:37.863
And per copy?
- Oh. jesus christ.

856
01:10:37.988 --> 01:10:39.208
Enough.

857
01:10:40.616 --> 01:10:42.117
What did he say?

858
01:10:50.501 --> 01:10:52.711
One million dollars.

859
01:10:54.505 --> 01:11:00.219
Added to statement of intent.
Portable Tetris goes to Mirrorsoft....

860
01:11:00.344 --> 01:11:03.555
provided you remit to us within a week
one million dollars.

861
01:11:05.015 --> 01:11:10.812
Well. gentlemen. it looks like we have a deal.

862
01:11:15.609 --> 01:11:17.069
I'll let you out.

863
01:11:17.194 --> 01:11:18.862
But we are not yet...
- Now.

864
01:11:24.576 --> 01:11:27.412
Mr. Belikov. the exit is over here.
- Shut up.

865
01:11:35.546 --> 01:11:36.766
Is everything okay?

866
01:11:38.382 --> 01:11:41.260
You have one week
to bid for the rights.

867
01:11:41.385 --> 01:11:44.555
You already know my bid.
I can sign right away. What is it?

868
01:11:44.680 --> 01:11:47.433
You must sign a letter of intent.
Protocol.

869
01:11:47.558 --> 01:11:50.060
Are you lying to me. Belikov?
- Listen.

870
01:11:50.185 --> 01:11:53.856
If you knew how much risk I am taking now.
you wouldn't ask.

871
01:11:54.898 --> 01:11:56.118
Please sign.

872
01:11:56.650 --> 01:11:57.870
Please.

873
01:12:02.614 --> 01:12:04.157
And one more thing.

874
01:12:04.950 --> 01:12:09.329
If you would like to bid
for the worldwide game console rights...

875
01:12:10.163 --> 01:12:13.625
ELORG is open to it.
- What? Those are already from Stein.

876
01:12:13.750 --> 01:12:14.970
No. not true.

877
01:12:15.544 --> 01:12:18.005
I redefined "computer.

878
01:12:19.173 --> 01:12:23.218
Stein wanted arcade rights.
so he signed a new contract.

879
01:12:24.011 --> 01:12:25.721
Why are you helping me. Belikov?

880
01:12:25.846 --> 01:12:28.599
I do what is best for my country.

881
01:12:29.892 --> 01:12:35.439
Go home. Henk Rogers. and come back
with the Nintendo people for a real bid.

882
01:12:45.657 --> 01:12:46.877
Where were you today?

883
01:12:47.951 --> 01:12:49.171
No matter.

884
01:12:49.620 --> 01:12:54.499
We did it. Portable rights.
and they also promise the game console rights.

885
01:12:57.336 --> 01:12:58.556
Get in.

886
01:12:59.838 --> 01:13:01.058
Dzerzhinski Square.

887
01:13:07.387 --> 01:13:09.014
Aren't you traveling by car?

888
01:13:10.557 --> 01:13:12.267
I don't want to be followed.

889
01:13:23.153 --> 01:13:27.866
When I was little. my father was
professor at the University of Moscow.

890
01:13:27.991 --> 01:13:32.120
In 1965. his colleague was jailed because
he sold his book abroad.

891
01:13:32.704 --> 01:13:34.289
Just for that?

892
01:13:35.249 --> 01:13:36.542
Yes.

893
01:13:36.667 --> 01:13:41.964
My father signed a letter of protest.
It was completely justified.

894
01:13:42.840 --> 01:13:45.175
But the state punished him for it.

895
01:13:45.884 --> 01:13:51.265
He was fired and never allowed to
have a good profession....

896
01:13:51.390 --> 01:13:54.977
And that destroyed him. And us. too.

897
01:13:55.477 --> 01:14:00.649
I promised myself that I would
would never do that to my children.

898
01:14:01.859 --> 01:14:03.569
But now they are doing it again.

899
01:14:04.528 --> 01:14:05.863
And this time with me.

900
01:14:15.998 --> 01:14:17.749
Do you know this building?

901
01:14:18.959 --> 01:14:23.046
They should.
They've been watching you the whole time.

902
01:14:26.466 --> 01:14:27.426
Wait. that...

903
01:14:27.551 --> 01:14:32.723
That's the guy from the Central Committee.
One of the most powerful men in the country.

904
01:14:32.848 --> 01:14:36.059
He talks to his agent.
- The KGB?

905
01:14:37.603 --> 01:14:38.823
Is Sasha from the KGB?

906
01:14:40.355 --> 01:14:41.575
But she...

907
01:14:42.941 --> 01:14:44.161
Why?

908
01:14:44.735 --> 01:14:46.028
You are a threat.

909
01:14:46.153 --> 01:14:50.157
You represent everything
that our country has been fighting against for 80 years.

910
01:14:52.242 --> 01:14:54.828
He just discovered
That ELORG promised you Tetris.

911
01:14:56.246 --> 01:14:58.081
The airport. Right now.

912
01:15:07.424 --> 01:15:11.762
It's important.
It's about Tetris. I'm in Korea right now.

913
01:15:11.887 --> 01:15:15.682
Sorry. they're having a meeting.
Can I pass something along?

914
01:15:15.807 --> 01:15:19.269
No. I want to say it myself.
I'll call them when I get home.

915
01:15:21.438 --> 01:15:25.025
Gentlemen. Robert Maxwell.
president of Mirror Group. Pleased to meet you.

916
01:15:25.150 --> 01:15:29.696
Minoru Arakawa. And this is Howard Lincoln.
vice president and legal counsel.

917
01:15:29.821 --> 01:15:31.365
What can we do for you?

918
01:15:34.076 --> 01:15:36.412
I believe I have something you want.

919
01:15:36.537 --> 01:15:38.831
Kevin. are you there?

920
01:15:38.956 --> 01:15:41.834
Yes. good news. gentlemen.

921
01:15:55.013 --> 01:15:56.974
FAX TO: HENK ROGERS
STATUS: COMPLETED

922
01:15:58.475 --> 01:16:00.936
You see. Nikolai Yevgenyevich....

923
01:16:01.061 --> 01:16:04.106
unlike you
I put our country first.

924
01:16:06.191 --> 01:16:09.152
Don't hoist him too heavily.
He still has work to do.

925
01:16:18.453 --> 01:16:20.414
Oh. shit.

926
01:16:22.624 --> 01:16:23.844
Maya?

927
01:16:30.632 --> 01:16:32.426
TETRIS HAS ENDED.
NIKOLAY BELIKOV

928
01:16:32.551 --> 01:16:34.761
Jesus. No.

929
01:16:46.398 --> 01:16:48.650
Oh. no.

930
01:16:48.775 --> 01:16:51.945
WE HAVE PICTURES. STAY AWAY.

931
01:16:56.200 --> 01:16:58.827
Hello?
- Henk. it's Howard Lincoln.

932
01:16:58.952 --> 01:17:01.955
I felt I should
to tell you in person.

933
01:17:03.749 --> 01:17:06.377
Too bad you
couldn't get those Game Boy rights.

934
01:17:06.502 --> 01:17:09.421
We buy them through Mirrorsoft.
You understand that. right?

935
01:17:11.006 --> 01:17:13.258
Hello?
- They're lying. Howard. Everybody lies.

936
01:17:13.383 --> 01:17:15.260
They blackmail me so I keep my mouth shut.

937
01:17:15.385 --> 01:17:18.138
Mirrorsoft doesn't even have
game console rights...

938
01:17:18.263 --> 01:17:22.309
We have a fax from ELORG confirming
that Mirrorsoft has the license.

939
01:17:22.434 --> 01:17:26.021
It's legitimate. Okay?
We'll look for something else again.

940
01:17:26.146 --> 01:17:28.398
Wait.
- Okay? Bye.

941
01:17:42.079 --> 01:17:43.330
Are you ready?

942
01:17:50.128 --> 01:17:54.925
The Maxwells took everything away from me.
- You missed your daughter's concert.

943
01:17:57.427 --> 01:17:59.012
Did you hear what I just said?

944
01:18:00.889 --> 01:18:02.933
Did you hear what I just said?

945
01:18:03.058 --> 01:18:05.310
We have nothing left.

946
01:18:05.435 --> 01:18:06.478
Nothing.

947
01:18:06.603 --> 01:18:09.731
And you're giving me a hard time
because I missed a concert?

948
01:18:11.275 --> 01:18:12.860
Maya.

949
01:18:14.319 --> 01:18:17.072
You selfish bastard.

950
01:18:17.656 --> 01:18:18.876
Honey?

951
01:18:20.450 --> 01:18:21.670
No worries.

952
01:18:22.327 --> 01:18:23.662
Everything will be fine.

953
01:18:25.247 --> 01:18:29.168
Because otherwise we have no
portable and gaming computer rights.

954
01:18:29.293 --> 01:18:31.128
Then Nintendo sues us...

955
01:18:31.253 --> 01:18:34.339
and we'll lose the company
and probably lose the house.

956
01:18:34.464 --> 01:18:39.261
And I'm trying to hold out hope. Akemi.
Really. But I don't have a plan B.

957
01:18:43.515 --> 01:18:48.812
Please understand that I did this
To build a life for us.

958
01:18:50.063 --> 01:18:52.774
We already had a life.

959
01:19:12.419 --> 01:19:14.630
May I come in?

960
01:19:16.715 --> 01:19:20.844
I have dedicated my life to this country.
To what it stands for.

961
01:19:22.012 --> 01:19:25.516
But ... I can't do it anymore.

962
01:19:26.099 --> 01:19:29.019
This country no longer exists.

963
01:19:30.604 --> 01:19:33.857
We are becoming a nation of thieves.

964
01:19:39.571 --> 01:19:41.865
Tetris goes to Mirrorsoft.

965
01:19:42.241 --> 01:19:46.203
And I will be fired from ELORG
as soon as the contract is signed.

966
01:19:48.247 --> 01:19:50.541
But you can still correct this.

967
01:19:56.630 --> 01:19:58.632
Send this to Henk Rogers.

968
01:20:00.133 --> 01:20:02.094
He knows what to do with it.

969
01:20:34.710 --> 01:20:35.930
Day.

970
01:20:36.378 --> 01:20:37.598
Day.

971
01:20:37.963 --> 01:20:39.183
Fire.

972
01:21:06.074 --> 01:21:07.294
What are you doing there?

973
01:21:45.572 --> 01:21:46.824
LETTER OF INTENT

974
01:21:46.949 --> 01:21:48.867
BIDDER PAYS $1.000.000 ...

975
01:21:48.992 --> 01:21:50.744
UPON TIMELY PAYMENT...

976
01:22:04.383 --> 01:22:06.510
Kevin. boy. Okay. gone.

977
01:22:06.635 --> 01:22:09.388
What happens here?
- We are cleaning up a bit.

978
01:22:09.513 --> 01:22:13.642
Those were unnecessary paperwork
for our accountants.

979
01:22:13.767 --> 01:22:18.355
How is it? Congratulations on Tetris.
- We don't have a million. accounting said.

980
01:22:18.480 --> 01:22:21.567
What do you need that for?
- Where... For Tetris.

981
01:22:21.692 --> 01:22:24.528
Boy. we don't have to
pay the Russians.

982
01:22:24.653 --> 01:22:26.530
They get the encyclopedias.

983
01:22:26.655 --> 01:22:29.491
No. no. no.
I had to promise them this.

984
01:22:29.616 --> 01:22:32.453
Listen. I am friends
With Mikhail Gorbachev.

985
01:22:32.578 --> 01:22:36.123
Please stop talking about Gorbachev.
The Soviet Union is on the verge of collapse.

986
01:22:36.248 --> 01:22:39.501
Everyone takes what he can
and Gorbachev can't do anything about it.

987
01:22:39.626 --> 01:22:42.629
Calm down. Kevin. No tantrums.
You're not a child.

988
01:22:44.256 --> 01:22:45.799
So don't treat me like that.

989
01:22:47.759 --> 01:22:50.596
We don't have the money. do we?
- Of course we do.

990
01:22:50.721 --> 01:22:52.181
Just not liquid.
- Okay.

991
01:22:52.306 --> 01:22:54.641
I call the bank for a loan.
- Bad idea.

992
01:22:54.766 --> 01:22:58.604
Jesus. You said everything was good.
- It is.

993
01:22:59.104 --> 01:23:03.192
As soon as we get Tetris
and sign the contract with Nintendo...

994
01:23:03.317 --> 01:23:04.735
everything is good again.
- Okay.

995
01:23:04.860 --> 01:23:07.696
But how do we get Tetris
without payment?

996
01:23:07.821 --> 01:23:10.115
Let me. Good job. kid.

997
01:23:19.499 --> 01:23:23.337
We are suing them. This really can't be done.
- This will not solve the problem.

998
01:23:23.462 --> 01:23:27.299
We will send a warning letter.
- Sir. Excuse me. you may not...

999
01:23:27.424 --> 01:23:29.593
There is a meeting.
- Not anymore.

1000
01:23:29.718 --> 01:23:31.845
What is he doing here?
- Reading.

1001
01:23:31.970 --> 01:23:33.931
No time for that.
- Reading.

1002
01:23:37.559 --> 01:23:39.937
What's that?
- Atari robbed us.

1003
01:23:40.062 --> 01:23:44.691
They hacked the NES and are selling
our cassettes. This is their first game.

1004
01:23:44.816 --> 01:23:47.486
They're not allowed to.
- They are in America.

1005
01:23:47.611 --> 01:23:49.279
No. not true.
- What?

1006
01:23:49.404 --> 01:23:52.491
Who is "A?
- Aleksey Pazhitnov.

1007
01:23:53.450 --> 01:23:57.704
'Henk. ELORG and Mirrorsoft lie.
No rights given for Tetris.

1008
01:23:57.829 --> 01:24:00.457
Come back and bid quickly.
What do you mean. no rights?

1009
01:24:00.582 --> 01:24:04.753
That's Mirrorsoft's contract.
A letter of intent that has expired.

1010
01:24:04.878 --> 01:24:06.338
So portable...
- Could still be.

1011
01:24:06.463 --> 01:24:07.881
And game consoles?
- Also.

1012
01:24:08.006 --> 01:24:09.299
Worldwide.
- But then...

1013
01:24:09.424 --> 01:24:12.052
I have no rights in Japan.
Stein and Mirrorsoft...

1014
01:24:12.177 --> 01:24:14.555
should not have sold them.
Not to them either.

1015
01:24:14.680 --> 01:24:19.852
So Atari doesn't have Tetris in America?
- Atari doesn't have Tetris anywhere at all.

1016
01:24:26.316 --> 01:24:29.194
How can you be sure
that this Aleksej is not lying?

1017
01:24:29.903 --> 01:24:32.906
Because he's the only one
who earns nothing from this.

1018
01:24:35.409 --> 01:24:36.493
What do you need.

1019
01:24:36.618 --> 01:24:40.622
I want you and your checkbooks
to come with me to Moscow.

1020
01:24:41.665 --> 01:24:43.083
And keep it a secret.

1021
01:24:51.091 --> 01:24:52.384
MOSKOU

1022
01:25:14.198 --> 01:25:17.492
He's here again. And he's not alone.

1023
01:25:18.160 --> 01:25:20.704
COMPUTER SCIENCE CENTER MOSCOW

1024
01:25:23.040 --> 01:25:24.260
Day.

1025
01:25:45.687 --> 01:25:48.607
What are you guys doing? What is this?

1026
01:25:52.110 --> 01:25:53.330
Damn.

1027
01:25:57.574 --> 01:26:00.077
Stop. What are you doing?

1028
01:26:03.205 --> 01:26:04.998
Sasha. what is happening?

1029
01:26:05.499 --> 01:26:06.959
You are moving.

1030
01:26:07.459 --> 01:26:11.213
Where to go? Why? I live here.
This is my childhood home. This can't be.

1031
01:26:11.338 --> 01:26:13.215
What is happening?

1032
01:26:14.466 --> 01:26:16.093
Your husband broke the law.

1033
01:26:17.594 --> 01:26:19.972
The school called
that the boys had been sent away.

1034
01:26:27.771 --> 01:26:31.191
Which one falls faster? Say.
- Neither.

1035
01:26:39.283 --> 01:26:40.325
Mom. Dad.

1036
01:26:40.450 --> 01:26:44.538
We learn about gravity.
He shows an experiment.

1037
01:26:45.122 --> 01:26:47.332
Exactly. An "experiment.

1038
01:26:50.627 --> 01:26:53.463
Which one falls faster? Speak up.
- The chair?

1039
01:26:54.673 --> 01:26:57.051
This is where gravity gets complicated.

1040
01:26:57.176 --> 01:27:00.762
Does the chair fall faster because it is heavy?
- Yes.

1041
01:27:01.388 --> 01:27:03.432
But no. Just listen.

1042
01:27:12.983 --> 01:27:16.070
It doesn't matter
Whether you're as light as a coin....

1043
01:27:16.195 --> 01:27:17.415
Or as heavy as...

1044
01:27:18.363 --> 01:27:19.583
a child.

1045
01:27:20.532 --> 01:27:22.451
Everything falls just as quickly.

1046
01:27:24.661 --> 01:27:26.205
Guys. start packing.

1047
01:27:35.380 --> 01:27:37.299
Henk Rogers is back because of you.

1048
01:27:41.303 --> 01:27:43.722
Spoiling your life was very easy.

1049
01:27:44.681 --> 01:27:48.894
If you cross me one more time.
you're finished.

1050
01:27:52.731 --> 01:27:54.107
Just like that Henk.

1051
01:28:13.710 --> 01:28:14.930
Mr. Belikov?

1052
01:28:17.089 --> 01:28:18.309
Is everything okay?

1053
01:28:19.508 --> 01:28:21.802
Apologies for being so late.

1054
01:28:29.434 --> 01:28:32.688
So you want to see new games?

1055
01:28:32.813 --> 01:28:35.357
No. We came for Tetris.

1056
01:28:37.442 --> 01:28:42.197
I have already informed you by fax that
the Tetris negotiations are over.

1057
01:28:44.783 --> 01:28:49.496
And I assume that you gave Mirrorsoft
the same deal that you gave to me.

1058
01:28:49.621 --> 01:28:52.833
One week to bid
on portable Tetris. Have they?

1059
01:28:54.793 --> 01:28:56.962
That's what I thought. Here's our bid.

1060
01:28:58.338 --> 01:29:02.009
For game console
and portable rights. worldwide.

1061
01:29:02.134 --> 01:29:05.596
We pay in advance. We pay
for all marketing and production.

1062
01:29:05.721 --> 01:29:10.642
You get 50 cents per copy sold.
both portable and for game consoles.

1063
01:29:13.645 --> 01:29:15.772
One dollar per copy.

1064
01:29:16.648 --> 01:29:20.235
Fine. We sign. and then we go.
- No.

1065
01:29:22.654 --> 01:29:25.616
I want what is best for our country.

1066
01:29:25.741 --> 01:29:30.579
Protecting government property
and decision-making is our job.

1067
01:29:33.540 --> 01:29:37.836
He says ELORG
needs time to read the contract.

1068
01:29:38.504 --> 01:29:39.838
That's the protocol.

1069
01:29:42.466 --> 01:29:43.686
That's right.

1070
01:29:44.635 --> 01:29:46.720
That's the protocol.

1071
01:29:49.598 --> 01:29:54.311
Good. Time to go. gentlemen.
I have another appointment.

1072
01:29:58.607 --> 01:30:00.609
Five million dollars?

1073
01:30:00.734 --> 01:30:03.195
And where is your payment. Mr. Maxwell?

1074
01:30:03.320 --> 01:30:06.782
I'm not going to fucking
pay five million dollars.

1075
01:30:06.907 --> 01:30:12.663
You don't have to. Just wire
the million your son promised.

1076
01:30:13.372 --> 01:30:14.998
Then Tetris is yours.

1077
01:30:15.707 --> 01:30:17.125
You have 24 hours.

1078
01:30:19.253 --> 01:30:21.880
Why must the Maxwells win?

1079
01:30:24.842 --> 01:30:28.554
Is the larger bid
not better for the Soviet Union?

1080
01:30:34.226 --> 01:30:37.938
Leave the fate of the Soviet Union
just leave it to me.

1081
01:30:39.523 --> 01:30:42.276
Just keep busy with your own work.

1082
01:30:45.112 --> 01:30:46.332
Dismissed.

1083
01:30:57.124 --> 01:30:59.376
Father.
- Not now.

1084
01:30:59.501 --> 01:31:03.422
Nintendo offers Russians five million
for game console and portable rights.

1085
01:31:03.547 --> 01:31:05.716
I know. Jo.
- Yeah.

1086
01:31:05.841 --> 01:31:09.970
Wait. Did you just say
portable and gaming computer rights?

1087
01:31:10.095 --> 01:31:11.055
Yes.
- You can't.

1088
01:31:11.180 --> 01:31:13.348
We have all the game console rights.

1089
01:31:13.473 --> 01:31:15.309
Purchased from...
- Kevin.

1090
01:31:15.434 --> 01:31:16.654
Asshole.

1091
01:31:17.436 --> 01:31:20.105
You were in Moscow.
You made a deal without me.

1092
01:31:20.230 --> 01:31:23.192
Now ELORG has changed my contract
and I have nothing.

1093
01:31:23.317 --> 01:31:26.570
Get security.
- And you. Robert.

1094
01:31:26.695 --> 01:31:29.615
I found Tetris.
Where is my compensation?

1095
01:31:29.740 --> 01:31:33.911
And thanks to your greed
the Russians put us out of business.

1096
01:31:34.036 --> 01:31:35.370
What are you talking about?

1097
01:31:35.954 --> 01:31:39.583
A new definition of "computer
in my contract.

1098
01:31:39.708 --> 01:31:42.753
Gone gaming computer rights.
so you could take them.

1099
01:31:42.878 --> 01:31:45.214
We have
no new gaming contract.

1100
01:31:47.424 --> 01:31:49.927
Oh. you dumbass.

1101
01:31:50.928 --> 01:31:52.638
Am I the dumbass here?

1102
01:31:53.263 --> 01:31:55.265
The spoiled billionaire's son...

1103
01:31:55.390 --> 01:31:59.186
Who has never worked a single day.
calls me a dummy?

1104
01:31:59.311 --> 01:32:01.480
You arrogant...

1105
01:32:07.569 --> 01:32:08.946
Come on. Let go of me.

1106
01:32:09.655 --> 01:32:12.407
Let go. Let go of me. Let go. Let go.

1107
01:32:14.409 --> 01:32:18.664
You. All of you.
You work for a bunch of thieves.

1108
01:32:19.873 --> 01:32:21.208
Thieves.

1109
01:32:21.333 --> 01:32:24.503
Jo. get the plane ready.

1110
01:32:25.087 --> 01:32:26.547
I'm going to Moscow.

1111
01:33:01.623 --> 01:33:03.959
Mr. Maxwell. Welcome to...

1112
01:33:08.297 --> 01:33:09.882
You again?

1113
01:33:15.387 --> 01:33:17.472
Gentlemen. Welcome.

1114
01:33:18.640 --> 01:33:24.021
Excuse me. I've gained some weight and need a
new suit for the ceremony today.

1115
01:33:24.146 --> 01:33:26.356
Looks good. Secretary General.

1116
01:33:26.481 --> 01:33:28.692
You are a bad liar. my friend.

1117
01:33:29.359 --> 01:33:30.861
What can I do for you?

1118
01:33:30.986 --> 01:33:33.447
Unfortunately. we don't come for fun.

1119
01:33:34.114 --> 01:33:38.327
My son and I are here because there is
an American businessman is in Moscow....

1120
01:33:38.452 --> 01:33:43.665
manipulating your bureaucrats for
the rights to a Russian computer game....

1121
01:33:43.790 --> 01:33:46.752
for which my company already had a deal.

1122
01:33:47.336 --> 01:33:52.674
In fact. he has just offered your people
just offered five million dollars.

1123
01:33:53.300 --> 01:33:54.259
And?

1124
01:33:54.384 --> 01:33:58.222
And if passed.
it sets a dangerous precedent.

1125
01:33:58.347 --> 01:33:59.567
What exactly?

1126
01:34:00.766 --> 01:34:03.352
That communism is dead.

1127
01:34:09.107 --> 01:34:11.985
So you've come to save my country?

1128
01:34:12.110 --> 01:34:16.031
Once you let capitalists in.
you never get rid of them.

1129
01:34:16.156 --> 01:34:17.658
And then what are you?

1130
01:34:17.783 --> 01:34:20.869
I am your friend. as you said.

1131
01:34:20.994 --> 01:34:25.165
We propose a fair exchange
where no money is involved.

1132
01:34:25.666 --> 01:34:29.336
You get the publishing rights
to Collier's Encyclopedia....

1133
01:34:29.461 --> 01:34:33.424
And we get the game.
An information exchange.

1134
01:34:33.549 --> 01:34:38.720
I appreciate your goodwill. Robert.
but my country is defective.

1135
01:34:39.346 --> 01:34:43.642
My people want freedom. They want
the right to vote. To control their own destiny.

1136
01:34:44.685 --> 01:34:48.522
It was never intended that
Communism to restrict freedom.

1137
01:34:48.647 --> 01:34:51.859
But unfortunately greed got in our way.

1138
01:34:53.318 --> 01:34:58.574
The world is changing. gentlemen.
and the Soviet Union will not be left behind.

1139
01:34:59.908 --> 01:35:02.828
I have to go.
I have to prepare my speech.

1140
01:35:05.080 --> 01:35:07.291
Do you want my advice?

1141
01:35:07.416 --> 01:35:12.129
With all due respect. we've made it this far
without you. so sod off.

1142
01:35:13.797 --> 01:35:16.008
Get me Tetris.

1143
01:35:16.842 --> 01:35:21.722
I want to know everything
what you know about that man.

1144
01:35:21.972 --> 01:35:23.473
About that foreigner?

1145
01:35:24.016 --> 01:35:27.561
No. About that politician.

1146
01:35:57.549 --> 01:36:01.386
Comrade Gorbachev.
look how much respect they show you.

1147
01:36:09.686 --> 01:36:10.906
Aleksej.

1148
01:36:11.480 --> 01:36:13.440
I already said I was coming back.

1149
01:36:15.025 --> 01:36:17.528
You shouldn't have come.
- What?

1150
01:36:18.195 --> 01:36:21.490
I'm here because of you.
- You had misunderstood me.

1151
01:36:22.991 --> 01:36:26.703
You literally wrote:
"Come back and make an offer soon.

1152
01:36:26.828 --> 01:36:29.581
I was wrong. You don't deserve it.

1153
01:36:30.290 --> 01:36:32.876
Aleksey. what is it? We are friends.
- No.

1154
01:36:33.585 --> 01:36:38.090
You used me to get your way.
- That... How can you say that?

1155
01:36:38.215 --> 01:36:41.677
I'm doing this for both of us.
- You're doing it for yourself.

1156
01:36:42.177 --> 01:36:45.973
I'm not making a dime on this.
- I'll take care of that.

1157
01:36:46.098 --> 01:36:48.892
It will...
- Don't promise what you can't give.

1158
01:36:52.062 --> 01:36:53.689
I come from a different world.

1159
01:36:55.357 --> 01:36:58.318
Go back to yours.
then I'll go back to mine.

1160
01:37:05.951 --> 01:37:10.289
Seventy years after our glorious revolution...

1161
01:37:11.290 --> 01:37:13.876
we live in a time of change.

1162
01:37:15.460 --> 01:37:18.839
But I am confident that the USSR...

1163
01:37:19.047 --> 01:37:20.632
Rogers goes to ELORG.

1164
01:37:21.842 --> 01:37:25.304
Will come out stronger.

1165
01:37:29.016 --> 01:37:30.236
Postage.

1166
01:37:32.102 --> 01:37:34.772
Where is Henk Rogers?
- On Bolshaya Ordynka.

1167
01:37:34.897 --> 01:37:37.316
Don't let him go to ELORG.

1168
01:37:37.441 --> 01:37:40.652
All agents to ELORG.
Repeat: All agents to ELORG.

1169
01:37:55.042 --> 01:37:57.211
This is not a counter-offer.

1170
01:37:57.336 --> 01:38:01.090
Correct.
This is our original and final bid.

1171
01:38:01.215 --> 01:38:03.717
Our rights for your rights.

1172
01:38:03.842 --> 01:38:07.429
And we want
the game console rights back. thank you.

1173
01:38:07.554 --> 01:38:10.140
What the hell?
- One choice.

1174
01:38:10.265 --> 01:38:15.145
A choice between your lousy deal
or our honest deal.

1175
01:38:19.107 --> 01:38:23.028
What?
- The relief troops are coming.

1176
01:38:23.153 --> 01:38:28.033
Our agreement guarantees us Tetris
if we make a counteroffer.

1177
01:38:28.158 --> 01:38:31.495
We did.
- Provided you pay a million.

1178
01:38:31.620 --> 01:38:33.997
Drop dead. Sign it.
- Follow the contract.

1179
01:38:34.122 --> 01:38:36.917
One more minute.
and then heads will roll.

1180
01:38:37.042 --> 01:38:41.171
Mr. Belikov. don't fall for it. All the...
- Father. just pay him now.

1181
01:38:44.675 --> 01:38:46.510
You don't have the money.

1182
01:38:46.635 --> 01:38:49.096
Therefore. you never pay fees.

1183
01:38:49.221 --> 01:38:51.265
What is going on?
- Nothing.

1184
01:38:52.432 --> 01:38:55.060
An administration problem
that will be fine.

1185
01:38:55.185 --> 01:38:56.395
So you are bankrupt.

1186
01:38:56.520 --> 01:38:58.897
Enough.
I can have you all arrested.

1187
01:38:59.022 --> 01:39:01.275
Can we just settle this now?

1188
01:39:01.400 --> 01:39:04.069
Mr. Belikov.
- You lout.

1189
01:39:06.280 --> 01:39:07.500
Way to go.

1190
01:39:11.451 --> 01:39:13.495
You are not safe in Moscow. Leave.

1191
01:39:29.553 --> 01:39:32.097
Where are they?
- They're gone. idiot.

1192
01:39:32.222 --> 01:39:33.557
What?
- With our deal.

1193
01:39:33.682 --> 01:39:37.603
Maxwell has no money. The contract
has expired. I had no choice.

1194
01:39:37.728 --> 01:39:43.275
I run a billion-dollar company.
Of course I have money.

1195
01:39:43.400 --> 01:39:47.196
Just not right now.
- What about my money?

1196
01:39:47.321 --> 01:39:50.574
How so 'your money'?
- Yes. how so 'your money'?

1197
01:39:51.325 --> 01:39:52.784
You can't be serious.

1198
01:39:54.119 --> 01:39:57.122
Did you bribe that jerk?
Behind my back?

1199
01:39:57.247 --> 01:39:59.374
Oh. shut up.

1200
01:39:59.499 --> 01:40:01.710
I came to your rescue. as usual.

1201
01:40:01.835 --> 01:40:07.132
Want to join the big boys?
That's how the world works. So don't whine.

1202
01:40:07.799 --> 01:40:12.805
Where's my money. Robert? I gave you
Tetris on a silver platter.

1203
01:40:12.930 --> 01:40:15.057
You only had to pay. Where is it?

1204
01:40:15.182 --> 01:40:18.602
We work for our country...
- You whore yourself out.

1205
01:40:20.020 --> 01:40:21.240
Good.

1206
01:40:21.688 --> 01:40:25.192
Give me back my contract
And I'll double your payment.

1207
01:40:25.317 --> 01:40:26.860
No.
- I triple it.

1208
01:40:26.985 --> 01:40:28.278
I don't trust your money.

1209
01:40:29.696 --> 01:40:31.615
I want to be a co-owner of Tetris.

1210
01:40:33.825 --> 01:40:35.045
Deal.

1211
01:40:39.248 --> 01:40:41.083
Rotten communists.

1212
01:40:51.468 --> 01:40:53.095
Get in.
- Come on.

1213
01:40:56.265 --> 01:40:57.891
Gone. gone. gone.

1214
01:41:12.698 --> 01:41:17.327
How did you know where we were?
- Simple. I thought: what would I never do?

1215
01:41:18.912 --> 01:41:20.132
Behind us.

1216
01:41:24.293 --> 01:41:25.513
Faster.

1217
01:41:38.265 --> 01:41:39.600
Aleksej.

1218
01:41:44.855 --> 01:41:46.732
What flights go like this?

1219
01:42:04.791 --> 01:42:06.585
We'll get this.
- It doesn't fit.

1220
01:42:07.836 --> 01:42:09.379
Do you trust me?

1221
01:42:13.300 --> 01:42:15.052
Oh. god.

1222
01:42:28.357 --> 01:42:29.577
Come on.

1223
01:43:00.931 --> 01:43:05.519
Flight 702 to Zurich is standing by.
Please proceed to the gate.

1224
01:43:07.688 --> 01:43:08.908
Next.

1225
01:43:10.107 --> 01:43:11.525
What is the next flight?

1226
01:43:12.359 --> 01:43:14.027
Send reinforcement.

1227
01:43:15.362 --> 01:43:16.582
Come with me.

1228
01:43:26.999 --> 01:43:31.837
Flight 802 to Tokyo is standing by.
Please proceed to the gate.

1229
01:43:35.340 --> 01:43:38.010
Come on. come on. come on.

1230
01:43:42.472 --> 01:43:43.807
They are coming.

1231
01:43:54.359 --> 01:43:55.152
Search.

1232
01:43:55.277 --> 01:43:56.779
Get out of here.
- No.

1233
01:43:56.904 --> 01:43:59.823
Not until you are gone.
- You've done enough.

1234
01:43:59.948 --> 01:44:01.950
Get out before they pick you up.

1235
01:44:02.868 --> 01:44:06.038
This is not a goodbye. I promise.

1236
01:44:07.956 --> 01:44:10.000
You don't like promises.

1237
01:44:10.125 --> 01:44:12.002
But I really mean it.

1238
01:44:13.170 --> 01:44:15.506
No. No time for American emotions.

1239
01:44:16.006 --> 01:44:17.257
Next.
- Go.

1240
01:44:20.928 --> 01:44:22.721
Reason for your trip?
- Tourism.

1241
01:44:38.403 --> 01:44:39.623
Excuse me.

1242
01:44:50.165 --> 01:44:53.293
Take a seat before departure.

1243
01:44:53.418 --> 01:44:54.503
On the side.

1244
01:44:54.628 --> 01:44:57.256
Where is the flight to Tokyo?
- Gate 6.

1245
01:44:57.381 --> 01:44:58.757
But it's closed.

1246
01:45:07.683 --> 01:45:09.643
Government Affairs.
- Belts on...

1247
01:45:10.352 --> 01:45:11.186
Open up.

1248
01:45:11.603 --> 01:45:15.607
Government Affairs.
- Sorry. we have some delay...

1249
01:45:18.110 --> 01:45:19.330
Now.

1250
01:45:24.157 --> 01:45:30.789
Welcome to Flight 802 to Tokyo.
We are almost ready to depart.

1251
01:45:30.914 --> 01:45:34.293
What?
- Buckle up.

1252
01:45:37.296 --> 01:45:38.516
Damn.

1253
01:45:39.965 --> 01:45:41.425
Wrong plane.

1254
01:45:54.313 --> 01:45:55.772
Valentin Igorovich.

1255
01:45:56.607 --> 01:45:59.234
By order of the secretary general

1256
01:45:59.359 --> 01:46:03.530
you are under arrest
for abuse of power and corruption.

1257
01:46:04.448 --> 01:46:06.366
No. What the hell?

1258
01:46:07.242 --> 01:46:10.496
Go away.
- You have broken the law.

1259
01:46:10.621 --> 01:46:11.955
I am the law.

1260
01:46:13.248 --> 01:46:14.468
Let me go.

1261
01:46:25.844 --> 01:46:28.680
Are you doing this
because I called you a whore?

1262
01:46:38.190 --> 01:46:40.859
Our country is finished. Do you hear me?

1263
01:46:41.193 --> 01:46:42.569
It ended.

1264
01:46:43.487 --> 01:46:46.573
Finished. It all collapses.

1265
01:46:49.493 --> 01:46:52.162
This is flight 702 to Zurich.

1266
01:46:52.287 --> 01:46:54.748
We wish you a pleasant flight.

1267
01:47:07.970 --> 01:47:10.764
CONGRATULATIONS

1268
01:47:10.889 --> 01:47:13.100
PLAYER 1

1269
01:47:13.225 --> 01:47:16.520
FINISHED THE GAME

1270
01:47:53.265 --> 01:47:54.516
Maya.

1271
01:47:58.061 --> 01:48:03.066
If you want to do it for me.
I'd like to hear the concert...

1272
01:48:03.942 --> 01:48:06.278
That I shouldn't have missed.

1273
01:48:16.914 --> 01:48:18.207
Please.

1274
01:48:30.344 --> 01:48:31.564
Okay.

1275
01:48:32.387 --> 01:48:33.764
I'm going to get ready.

1276
01:48:40.020 --> 01:48:44.274
I had promised something.
That didn't go as I hoped.

1277
01:48:50.989 --> 01:48:52.616
But now I do.

1278
01:49:00.123 --> 01:49:02.125
BULLET-PROOF SOFTWARE
FIVE MILLION DOLLARS

1279
01:49:26.525 --> 01:49:29.403
This is going to be an exciting Christmas...

1280
01:49:29.528 --> 01:49:32.948
With a brand new gift under the tree.
The Game Boy.

1281
01:49:33.073 --> 01:49:36.827
There are demonstrations all over
the Soviet Union are demonstrating.

1282
01:49:36.952 --> 01:49:40.205
Nintendo
has already sold out twice in Japan.

1283
01:49:40.330 --> 01:49:43.125
And that seems to be happening in America as well....

1284
01:49:43.250 --> 01:49:47.171
where the proceeds for the holidays
is already over $110 million.

1285
01:49:47.296 --> 01:49:50.132
And the demand
does not seem to be decreasing by a long shot.

1286
01:49:50.257 --> 01:49:53.802
All over Eastern Europe
the borders are opening up.

1287
01:49:53.927 --> 01:49:56.930
This is due in part to Tetris....

1288
01:49:57.055 --> 01:50:00.642
the new top game
that the whole family wants to play.

1289
01:50:01.268 --> 01:50:06.064
Gorbachev has resigned.
The red flag hangs at half-mast in the Kremlin.

1290
01:50:13.488 --> 01:50:15.365
Good news or bad news?

1291
01:50:18.660 --> 01:50:20.204
I think both.

1292
01:50:21.538 --> 01:50:23.373
A package for you. From Henk.

1293
01:50:37.596 --> 01:50:38.555
ALEKSEY PAZHITNOV

1294
01:50:38.680 --> 01:50:41.099
FROM: MOSCOW
TO: SAN FRANCISCO

1295
01:50:42.809 --> 01:50:45.103
five minutes. Mom needs "the bed.

1296
01:50:45.646 --> 01:50:47.189
There they are.

1297
01:50:56.907 --> 01:50:58.617
Welcome to your new home.

1298
01:50:59.201 --> 01:51:02.538
Is this a better time
for American emotions?

1299
01:51:12.422 --> 01:51:15.759
Henk and Aleksej later founded
The Tetris Company.

1300
01:51:15.884 --> 01:51:18.512
Robert Stein has continued
selling licenses.

1301
01:51:18.637 --> 01:51:20.806
He's still upset
that he missed out on Tetris.

1302
01:51:20.931 --> 01:51:24.309
Robert Maxwell stole 900 million
From corporate pension fund...

1303
01:51:24.434 --> 01:51:30.607
and had debts of more than five billion.
which caused his media empire to collapse.

1304
01:51:30.732 --> 01:51:34.695
After Robert Maxwell's unexplained death
Kevin Maxwell was arrested

1305
01:51:34.820 --> 01:51:39.950
in connection with
his father's pension robbery and bankruptcy.

1306
01:51:40.075 --> 01:51:44.580
He was later tried for fraud .
but was acquitted.

1307
01:51:44.705 --> 01:51:49.001
In 2014. Henk appointed his daughter Maya
appointed as the new director of Tetris.

1308
01:51:52.045 --> 01:51:56.967
With half a billion copies sold
it is one of the most popular games ever.

1309
01:54:08.557 --> 01:54:10.851
The TV doesn't work.
Neither does the video player.

1310
01:54:12.269 --> 01:54:16.982
I have already read everything.
After this we will go to the Moscow Go club.

1311
01:54:17.482 --> 01:54:18.859
Your name is Alla?

1312
01:54:19.568 --> 01:54:22.571
Alla takes us
to the Russian Go association.

1313
01:54:22.696 --> 01:54:25.657
And she also found ELORG for us.

1314
01:54:25.782 --> 01:54:27.659
This is Aleksey Pazhitnov.

1315
01:54:27.784 --> 01:54:30.370
The creator of Tetris.
- Well. sort of.

1316
01:54:30.495 --> 01:54:33.791
I play Tetris with my friends.

1317
01:54:33.916 --> 01:54:35.292
Okay.

1318
01:57:14.618 --> 01:57:16.620
Translation: Lorien Franssen
